histogram.name: Accessibility.CrosAlwaysShowA11yMenu
histogram.summary: Whether the Chrome OS Accessibility Menu is set to be shown regardless of the state of a11y features.(checked once 45 secs after startup).

histogram.name: Accessibility.CrosAutoclick
histogram.summary: Whether the Chrome OS Autoclick feature is on (checked once 45 secs after startup).

histogram.name: Accessibility.CrosAutoclickDelay
histogram.summary: If the user has enabled Autoclick, this is the delay set by the user for autoclicks to occur, in milliseconds.

histogram.name: Accessibility.CrosHighContrast
histogram.summary: Whether the Chrome OS High Contrast mode feature is on (checked once 45 secs after startup).

histogram.name: Accessibility.CrosLargeCursor
histogram.summary: Whether the Chrome OS Large Cursor feature is on (checked once 45 secs after startup).

histogram.name: Accessibility.CrosScreenMagnifier
histogram.summary: Whether the Chrome OS Screen Magnifier feature is on (checked once 45 secs after startup).

histogram.name: Accessibility.CrosSpokenFeedback
histogram.summary: Whether the Chrome OS Spoken Feedback feature is on (checked once 45 secs after startup).

histogram.name: Accessibility.CrosVirtualKeyboard
histogram.summary: Whether the Chrome OS Virtual Keyboard feature is on (checked once 45 secs after startup).

histogram.name: Accessibility.InvertedColors
histogram.summary: Whether Windows system settings show that high-contrast mode is enabled and the user has selected a light-on-dark color scheme (checked once 45 secs after startup). This causes Chrome to prompt the user with a bubble to optionally install a High Contrast extension and theme.

histogram.name: Accessibility.ManuallyEnabled
histogram.summary: Whether Chrome has enabled accessibility support because the user passed the --force-renderer-accessibility flag on the command-line (checked once 45 secs after startup).

histogram.name: Accessibility.State
histogram.summary: Whether Chrome has enabled accessibility support because it detects supported assistive technology running, or due to being manually enabled via a command-line flag (checked once 45 secs after startup).

histogram.name: Accessibility.WinAudioDescription
histogram.summary: Whether Windows system settings show that audio descriptions are enabled (checked once 45 secs after startup).

histogram.name: Accessibility.WinJAWS
histogram.summary: Whether the third-party JAWS screen reader is running (checked once 45 secs after startup).

histogram.name: Accessibility.WinNVDA
histogram.summary: Whether the third-party NVDA screen reader is running (checked once 45 secs after startup).

histogram.name: Accessibility.WinSAToGo
histogram.summary: Whether the third-party System Access To Go screen reader is running (checked once 45 secs after startup).

histogram.name: Accessibility.WinScreenReader
histogram.summary: Whether Windows system settings show that a screen reader is running (checked once 45 secs after startup). Note that this does not necessarily mean that Chrome has detected a supported screen reader and has enabled its accessibility mode.

histogram.name: Accessibility.WinStickyKeys
histogram.summary: Whether Windows system settings show that Sticky Keys are enabled.

histogram.name: Accessibility.WinZoomText
histogram.summary: Whether the third-party ZoomText screen magnifier is running.

histogram.name: Apps.AppLaunch
histogram.summary: The number of times v2 packaged apps are launched grouped by extension_misc::AppLaunchBuckets. See also Extensions.AppLaunch.

histogram.name: Apps.AppLauncherPromo
histogram.summary: Interactions with the App Launcher promo dialog.

histogram.name: Apps.AppListSearchCommenced
histogram.summary: The number of searches that are started in the app list. This is gathered each time the app list search box transitions from empty to non-empty.

histogram.name: Apps.AppListSearchResultOpenType
histogram.summary: The type of app list search result that was opened by the user. This is gathered per click of a search result.

histogram.name: Ash.ActiveTouchPoints
histogram.summary: Number of active touch-points when a new touch-point is added.

histogram.name: Ash.ActiveWindowShowTypeOverTime
histogram.summary: The show type of the active window tracked over time by logging on a regular basis (30 minutes).

histogram.name: Ash.Dock.Action
histogram.summary: User-initiated action taken that affects docked windows such as docking, undocking, minimizing, restoring, closing or just dragging a docked window.

histogram.name: Ash.Dock.ActionSource
histogram.summary: Source (mouse, touch or unknown) of the user-initiated action for docked windows.

histogram.name: Ash.Dock.ItemsAll
histogram.summary: Number of all docked windows or panels including hidden or minimized. Recorded on every user action that interacts with docked windows.

histogram.name: Ash.Dock.ItemsLarge
histogram.summary: Number of large (wider than dock maximum width) windows that had to be shrunk to get docked among the visible docked windows. Recorded on every user action that interacts with docked windows.

histogram.name: Ash.Dock.ItemsPanels
histogram.summary: Number of docked visible panels. Recorded on every user action that interacts with docked windows.

histogram.name: Ash.Dock.ItemsVisible
histogram.summary: Number of visible docked windows or panels. Recorded on every user action that interacts with docked windows.

histogram.name: Ash.Dock.TimeBetweenUse
histogram.summary: Time elapsed between instances of docking, undocking or any other action affecting docked state of a window.

histogram.name: Ash.Dock.Width
histogram.summary: Width of the docked area in pixels. Recorded every time it changes after a user window resize operation is completed.

histogram.name: Ash.GestureCreated
histogram.summary: The gesture-events recognized and dispatched by the browser gesture recognizer.

histogram.name: Ash.GestureTarget
histogram.summary: The gesture-events recognized and dispatched by the browser gesture recognizer for various UI components.

histogram.name: Ash.ImmersiveFullscreen.WindowType
histogram.summary: The type of the window which is put into immersive fullscreen. Immersive fullscreen is entered via the F4 key.

histogram.name: Ash.ShelfAlignmentOverTime
histogram.summary: The current state of the shelf (alignment) tracked over time by logging on a regular basis (30 minutes), this is used instead of log in or shelf usage to track users that do not lock/unlock or log in frequently and use a small number of browser instances or otherwise infrequently interact with the shelf launcher.

histogram.name: Ash.ShelfAlignmentUsage
histogram.summary: The current state of the shelf (alignment) when the shelf launcher is used to launch an app/window/etc, this is used instead of log in to give data on users that do not lock/unlock or log in frequently.

histogram.name: Ash.TouchDuration
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated 12/2013 in r239809, and replaced by Ash.TouchDuration2.
histogram.summary: The duration of a touch-sequence.

histogram.name: Ash.TouchDuration2
histogram.summary: The duration of a touch-sequence.

histogram.name: Ash.TouchMoveInterval
histogram.summary: The interval between touch-move events.

histogram.name: Ash.TouchMoveSteps
histogram.summary: The distance between touch-move events.

histogram.name: Ash.TouchPositionX
histogram.summary: The position of the touch-events along the X axis.

histogram.name: Ash.TouchPositionY
histogram.summary: The position of the touch-events along the Y axis.

histogram.name: Ash.TouchRadius
histogram.summary: The radius of a touch event.

histogram.name: Ash.TouchStartAfterEnd
histogram.summary: The interval between the end of a touch-sequence and the start of the next touch-sequence.

histogram.name: Ash.TouchStartBurst
histogram.summary: The number of rapid touch-starts that happened within a short interval. Logged once for each such burst group.

histogram.name: Ash.WindowSelector.CycleTime
histogram.summary: The amount of time the Alt key is held after pressing Alt+Tab to begin cycling through windows.

histogram.name: Ash.WindowSelector.Items
histogram.summary: The number of items (single windows or groups of windows such as panels) in the window selection. Window selection occurs when a user begins alt-tabbing or presses the overview button (F5 key).

histogram.name: Ash.WindowSelector.TimeBetweenUse
histogram.summary: The amount of time between uses of window selection to switch between windows. Window selection is entered by alt-tabbing or by pressing the overview button (F5 key).

histogram.name: Ash.WindowSelector.TimeInOverview
histogram.summary: The amount of time spent in overview mode. Overview mode is engaged when lingering on a window while alt-tabbing or by pressing the overview button. The time is measured from the moment the windows begin animating to a thumbnail size preview to when a window is selected or selection is canceled.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.AttemptCountFail
histogram.summary: Count of DnsAttempts before DnsTransaction completes with failure.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.AttemptCountSuccess
histogram.summary: Count of DnsAttempts before DnsTransaction completes successfully.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ConfigChange
histogram.summary: Whether DnsConfigService::OnConfigChange actually corresponded to a change in DnsConfig.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ConfigNotifyInterval
histogram.summary: Duration of time between calls to DnsConfigService::InvalidateConfig.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ConfigParseDuration
histogram.summary: Duration of time spent parsing DnsConfig.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ConfigParsePosix
histogram.summary: Counts of results of parsing DnsConfig in DnsConfigServicePosix.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ConfigParseResult
histogram.summary: Whether DnsConfig was parsed successfully.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ConfigParseWin
histogram.summary: Counts of results of parsing DnsConfig in DnsConfigServiceWin.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.DNSChangerDetected
histogram.summary: Whether the first valid DnsConfig included a rogue nameserver.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.DnsClientDisabledReason
histogram.summary: Counts of specific error codes returned by DnsTask if a subsequent ProcTask succeeded, at the end of a streak of failures after which the DnsClient was disabled.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.DnsClientEnabled
histogram.summary: TRUE counts the events when a valid DnsConfig is received and used to enable DnsClient, while FALSE counts the events when DnsClient is disabled after a series of successful fallbacks from DnsTask to ProcTask.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.FallbackFail
histogram.summary: Duration of time spent by ProcTask in failing fallback resolutions.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.FallbackSuccess
histogram.summary: Duration of time spent by ProcTask in successful fallback resolutions.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.HaveDnsConfig
histogram.summary: Whether there was a valid DNS configuration at the start of a job which eventually completed successfully.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.HostParseResult
histogram.summary: Whether DnsHosts were parsed successfully.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.HostsChange
histogram.summary: Whether DnsConfigService::OnHostsChange actually corresponded to a change in DnsHosts.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.HostsNotifyInterval
histogram.summary: Duration of time between calls to DnsConfigService::InvalidateHosts.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.HostsParseDuration
histogram.summary: Duration of time spent parsing DnsHosts.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.HostsParseWin
histogram.summary: Counts of results of parsing DnsHosts in DnsConfigServiceWin.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.HostsSize
histogram.summary: The size of the HOSTS file observed before each attempt to parse it.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.JobQueueTime
histogram.summary: Time elapsed between the time the HostResolverImpl::Job was created and the time the Job was started (using DnsClient).

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.JobQueueTime_HIGHEST
histogram.summary: Time elapsed between the time the HostResolverImpl::Job was created and the time the Job was started (using DnsClient). Includes only Jobs which had priority HIGHEST when started.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.JobQueueTime_IDLE
histogram.summary: Time elapsed between the time the HostResolverImpl::Job was created and the time the Job was started (using DnsClient). Includes only Jobs which had priority IDLE when started.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.JobQueueTime_LOW
histogram.summary: Time elapsed between the time the HostResolverImpl::Job was created and the time the Job was started (using DnsClient). Includes only Jobs which had priority LOW when started.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.JobQueueTime_LOWEST
histogram.summary: Time elapsed between the time the HostResolverImpl::Job was created and the time the Job was started (using DnsClient). Includes only Jobs which had priority LOWEST when started.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.JobQueueTime_MEDIUM
histogram.summary: Time elapsed between the time the HostResolverImpl::Job was created and the time the Job was started (using DnsClient). Includes only Jobs which had priority MEDIUM when started.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.JobQueueTimeAfterChange
histogram.summary: Time elapsed between the last time the priority of a HostResolverImpl::Job changed (when a Request was attached or detached) and the time the Job was started (using DnsClient).

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.JobQueueTimeAfterChange_HIGHEST
histogram.summary: Time elapsed between the last time the priority of a HostResolverImpl::Job changed (when a Request was attached or detached) and the time the Job was started (using DnsClient). Includes only Jobs which had priority HIGHEST when started.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.JobQueueTimeAfterChange_IDLE
histogram.summary: Time elapsed between the last time the priority of a HostResolverImpl::Job changed (when a Request was attached or detached) and the time the Job was started (using DnsClient). Includes only Jobs which had priority IDLE when started.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.JobQueueTimeAfterChange_LOW
histogram.summary: Time elapsed between the last time the priority of a HostResolverImpl::Job changed (when a Request was attached or detached) and the time the Job was started (using DnsClient). Includes only Jobs which had priority LOW when started.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.JobQueueTimeAfterChange_LOWEST
histogram.summary: Time elapsed between the last time the priority of a HostResolverImpl::Job changed (when a Request was attached or detached) and the time the Job was started (using DnsClient). Includes only Jobs which had priority LOWEST when started.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.JobQueueTimeAfterChange_MEDIUM
histogram.summary: Time elapsed between the last time the priority of a HostResolverImpl::Job changed (when a Request was attached or detached) and the time the Job was started (using DnsClient). Includes only Jobs which had priority MEDIUM when started.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ParseToAddressList
histogram.summary: Counts of results of parsing addresses out of DNS responses in successful DnsTransactions.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ResolveError
histogram.summary: Counts of specific error codes returned by DnsTask if a subsequent ProcTask succeeded.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ResolveFail
histogram.summary: Duration of time taken by DnsTask in resolutions that failed. Excludes time spent in the subsequent fallback.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ResolveStatus
histogram.summary: Counts of the overall results of using asynchronous DNS in HostResolverImpl. This only includes jobs started with valid DNS configuration and excludes synchronous resolutions (as IP literals, from cache, and from HOSTS).

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ResolveSuccess
histogram.summary: Duration of time taken by DnsTask in resolutions that succeeded.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ResolveSuccess_FAMILY_IPV4
histogram.summary: Same as AsyncDNS.ResolveSuccess, but limited to pure IPv4 lookups.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ResolveSuccess_FAMILY_IPV6
histogram.summary: Same as AsyncDNS.ResolveSuccess, but limited to pure IPv6 lookups.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ResolveSuccess_FAMILY_UNSPEC
histogram.summary: Same as AsyncDNS.ResolveSuccess, but limited to IPv4/IPv6 lookups.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ServerCount
histogram.summary: Count of servers in DnsConfig. Recorded on every new DnsSession, which is created on DNS change.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ServerFailureIndex
histogram.summary: Index in DnsConfig of the failing server, recorded at the time of failure.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ServerFailuresAfterNetworkChange
histogram.summary: Count of server failures after network change before first success in the DnsSession. Recorded at the time of first success.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ServerFailuresAfterSuccess
histogram.summary: Count of server failures after success until the end of the session. Server has reported success at some point during the session. Recorded at the end of the DnsSession.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ServerFailuresBeforeSuccess
histogram.summary: Count of server failures before success. This is NOT the first success in the DnsSession. Recorded at the time of success.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ServerFailuresWithoutSuccess
histogram.summary: Count of server failures without success until the end of the session. Server has never reported success during the DnsSession. Recorded at the end of the DnsSession.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.ServerIsGood
histogram.summary: The current server is "good" and does not have to be skipped.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.SortFailure
histogram.summary: Duration of time taken in failing calls to AddressSorter in dual-stack resolutions using DnsTask.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.SortSuccess
histogram.summary: Duration of time taken in successful calls to AddressSorter in dual-stack resolutions using DnsTask.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.SuffixSearchDone
histogram.summary: The number of names from the search name list consumed during a successful transaction (QTYPE A only).

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.SuffixSearchRemain
histogram.summary: The number of names left on the search name list at the end of a successful transaction (QTYPE A only).

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.SuffixSearchStart
histogram.summary: The number of names on the search name list at the start of a transaction (QTYPE A only).

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TCPAttemptFail
histogram.summary: Duration of time taken by DnsTCPAttempt in failed attempts. Excludes timeouts.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TCPAttemptSuccess
histogram.summary: Duration of time taken by DnsTCPAttempt in successful attempts.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TimeoutErrorHistogram
histogram.summary: Difference between RTT and timeout calculated using Histogram algorithm.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TimeoutErrorHistogramUnder
histogram.summary: Difference between timeout calculated using Histogram algorithm and RTT.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TimeoutErrorJacobson
histogram.summary: Difference between RTT and timeout calculated using Jacobson algorithm.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TimeoutErrorJacobsonUnder
histogram.summary: Difference between timeout calculated using Jacobson algorithm and RTT.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TimeoutSpentHistogram
histogram.summary: Duration of time that would be spent waiting for lost request using Histogram algorithm.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TimeoutSpentJacobson
histogram.summary: Duration of time that would be spent waiting for lost request using Jacobson algorithm.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TotalTime
histogram.summary: Duration of time since a HostResolverImpl::Resolve request to the time a result is posted. Excludes canceled, evicted, and aborted requests. Includes cache hits (recorded as 0). Excludes speculative requests.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TotalTime_speculative
histogram.summary: Duration of time since a HostResolverImpl::Resolve request to the time a result is posted. Excludes canceled, evicted, and aborted requests. Includes cache hits (recorded as 0). Speculative requests only.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TransactionFailure
histogram.summary: Duration of time taken in failing DnsTransactions. This includes server failures, timeouts and NXDOMAIN results.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TransactionSuccess
histogram.summary: Duration of time taken in successful DnsTransactions. This includes all NOERROR answers, even if they indicate the name has no addresses or they cannot be parsed.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TransactionSuccess_A
histogram.summary: Same as AsyncDNS.TransactionSuccess but limited to A query type.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TransactionSuccess_AAAA
histogram.summary: Same as AsyncDNS.TransactionSuccess but limited to AAAA query type.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.TTL
histogram.summary: TTL of the resolved addresses, as in the response received from the server. For results served from local cache, the TTL is from the original response.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.UDPAttemptFail
histogram.summary: Duration of time taken by DnsUDPAttempt in failed attempts. Excludes timeouts.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.UDPAttemptSuccess
histogram.summary: Duration of time taken by DnsUDPAttempt in successful attempts. Includes responses arriving after timeout, if multiple attempts are allowed.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.UnchangedConfigInterval
histogram.summary: Duration of time since the last empty config result to the time a non-change OnConfigChange is received.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.UnchangedHostsInterval
histogram.summary: Duration of time since the last empty config result to the time a non-change OnHostsChange is received.

histogram.name: AsyncDNS.WatchStatus
histogram.summary: The result of DnsConfigService watch. Counts STARTED on every initialization and FAILED_* on any failure.

histogram.name: Aura.CreatedGpuBrowserCompositor

histogram.name: ConnectivityDiagnostics.ChromeOsSignalStrength
histogram.summary: Connectivity Diagnostics App: WiFi signal strength recorded during NIC_SIGNAL_STRENGTH test.
histogram.details: The "Strength" property of a WiFi signal is a partially-reversible function that linearly maps the RSSI range -120dBm to -20dBm to Strength values from 0 to 100.

histogram.name: ConnectivityDiagnostics.HTTP_LATENCY
histogram.summary: HTTP latency seen by the Connectivity Diagnostics.
histogram.details: HTTP latency is computed using the chrome.socket API to make an HTTP GET request to the /generate_204 page of three randomly generated Google hostnames (*-ccd-testing-v4.metric.gstatic.com). The time taken from issuing the HTTP request to receiving a response is clocked in JavaScript and the arithmetic mean of the three times is used as the HTTP latency.

histogram.name: ConnectivityDiagnostics.RESOLVER_LATENCY
histogram.summary: Resolution latency seen by the Connectivity Diagnostics.
histogram.details: Resolver latency is computed by using the chrome.dns API to query three randomly generated Google hostnames (*-ccd-testing-v4.metric.gstatic.com). The random hostnames guarantees that there will be no caching of DNS hostnames. The time taken from issuing the DNS request to receiving a response is clocked in JavaScript and the arithmetic mean of the three times is used as the resolver latency.

histogram.name: ConnectivityDiagnostics.TestVerdict
histogram.summary: Connectivity Diagnostics App: Outcome of the connectivity tests.

histogram.name: ConnectivityDiagnostics.TimeTaken

histogram.name: Cookie.ParsedCookieStatus
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 9/2013. Experiment to measure control characters in cookies is finished.
histogram.summary: When parsing a cookie, indicates if control characters were present in any of the cookie values and if any of the cookie values were invalid. Specifically, checks that all of the parsed values are valid according to the valid token definition in Section 2.2 of RFC2616 which specifies a token must have no separators (i.e. no characters from the following string, ignoring the starting and ending single quote: '()<>@,;:\"/[]?={} \t') and no control characters.

histogram.name: Cookie.ReinstatedCookies
histogram.summary: The duration in seconds between a cookie getting evicted (due to the number of cookies exceeding a domain limit), and subsequently reinstated.

histogram.name: Cookie.SetAttributePairCharsValidity
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 9/2013. Experiment to measure control characters in cookies is finished.
histogram.summary: Indicates whether a cookie attribute pair was set with both a valid key and a valid attribute value or not. For the key, this implies that it was a valid token as defined in Section 2.2 of RFC2616 which specifies a token must have no separators (i.e. no characters from the following string, ignoring the starting and ending single quote: '()<>@,;:\"/[]?={} \t') and no control characters. For the value, this implies that it contained no control characters and no semicolon.

histogram.name: Cookie.SetNameValidity
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 9/2013. Experiment to measure control characters in cookies is finished.
histogram.summary: Indicates whether a cookie name was set with a valid token. A valid token is defined in Section 2.2 of RFC2616 which specifies a token must have no separators (i.e. no characters from the following string, ignoring the starting and ending single quote: '()<>@,;:\"/[]?={} \t') and no control characters.

histogram.name: Cookie.SetValueCookieValueValidity
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 9/2013. Experiment to measure control characters in cookies is finished.
histogram.summary: Indicates whether a cookie value was valid or invalid when there was an attempt to set it, where a valid value is defined in RFC 6265 as ASCII characters excluding controls, whitspace, comma, semicolon, and backslash.

In newer versions, if the hostname has never been found as a link during a page scan, and it has a referring URL, then it is added to referrer list data structure (hoping we'll do better next time).

histogram.name: DNS.IndependentNavigation

histogram.name: DNS.PrefetchCacheEviction

histogram.name: DNS.PrefetchFoundName
histogram.summary: Replaced by DNS.PrefetchFoundNameL.

histogram.name: DNS.PrefetchFoundNameL
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated 2/2010, and replaced by DNS.PrefetchResolution
histogram.summary: The duration of time used by the DNS pre-resolving threads to resolve a host name via the network. Any resolutions that are faster than 15ms are considered to be local cache hits, not requiring network access, and are not included in this histogram. This histogram is most useful for estimating the typical cost of a name resolution, but it also estimates the total number of network-based resolutions induced by this feature. Not all these resolutions prove helpful (i.e., the user does not always actually visit the resolved hostnames).

histogram.name: DNS.PrefetchNegativeHit
histogram.summary: Replaced by DNS.PrefetchNegativeHitL.

histogram.name: DNS.PrefetchNegativeHitL
histogram.summary: The duration of time saved due to DNS pre-resolving in the "name not found" case. Time "savings" shown in the histogram are defined to be the difference between the DNS pre-resolution duration, and the DNS resolution duration seen during a navigation. These cache hits only list events where the DNS pre-resolve duration for a host was in excess of 15ms (i.e., the network was consulted), and the actual DNS resolution (when a user attempted to navigate to a link with the same host name) took less than 15ms (i.e., the network was not consulted), which means the gain was a result of a "cache hit" in the OS cache. For some users with LANs, all negative results (even when the DNS cache might otherwise help) take about 2.5 seconds (due to timeouts for netbios broadcasts), and hence no savings are possible (or shown) for such users in this category.

histogram.name: DNS.PrefetchPositiveHit
histogram.summary: Replaced by DNS.PrefetchPositiveHitL.

histogram.name: DNS.PrefetchPositiveHitL
histogram.summary: The duration of time saved due to DNS pre-resolving in the "name was found" case, and induced by either a page scan for a link or an omnibox entry by the user. Time "savings" shown in the histogram are defined to be the difference between the DNS pre-resolution duration, and the DNS resolution duration seen during a navigation. These cache hits only list events where the DNS pre-resolve duration for a host was in excess of 15ms (i.e., the network was consulted), and the actual DNS resolution (when a user attempted to navigate to a link with the same host name) took less than 15ms (i.e., the network was not consulted), which means the gain was a result of a "cache hit" in the OS cache.

histogram.name: DNS.PrefetchQueue
histogram.summary: The duration of time spent by a proposed resolution waiting in the queue to be resolved. This number is in addition to any DNS resolution time that may come later.

histogram.name: DNS.PrefetchReferredPositiveHit
histogram.summary: The duration of time saved due to DNS pre-resolving in the "name was found" case, and induced by predicting (using referrer lists) that a resolution was needed. Time "savings" shown in the histogram are defined to be the difference between the DNS pre-resolution duration, and the DNS resolution duration seen during a navigation. These cache hits only list events where the DNS pre-resolve duration for a host was in excess of 15ms (i.e., the network was consulted), and the actual DNS resolution (when a user attempted to navigate to a link with the same host name) took less than 15ms (i.e., the network was not consulted), which means the gain was a result of a "cache hit" in the OS cache.

histogram.name: DNS.PrefetchResolution
histogram.summary: The duration of time used by the DNS pre-resolving threads to resolve a host name via the network. Any resolutions that are faster than 15ms are considered to be local cache hits, not requiring network access, and are not included in this histogram. This histogram is most useful for estimating the typical cost of a name resolution, but it also estimates the total number of network-based resolutions induced by this feature. Not all these resolutions prove helpful (i.e., the user does not always actually visit the resolved hostnames).

histogram.name: DNS.QueueRecycledUnder2
histogram.summary: When, due to congestion avoidance, a queued pre-resolution is abandoned (recycled) without actually being resolved, this histograms records the age in the queue of that entry. Only times less than or equal to 2 seconds are recorded in this histogram.

histogram.name: DNS.UnexpectedResolution
histogram.summary: In some cases, such as when content arrives with embedded references to other servers, the prefetch system can't (or doesn't) attempt to pre-resolve the hostnames. As an example, a visit to www.cnn.com will fetch content with references to about 12 additional hostnames, none of which are currently anticipated. Such resolutions are termed "Unexpected Resolutions," and the durations associated with those DNS resolutions are shown below. Future features may attempt to learn (from prior experience locally, or from server provided hints), what secondary hostname resolutions should be done when a primary resolution (or navigation) takes place. This histogram shows what the potential savings are that "remain on the table" until we employ some of these more advanced features.

histogram.name: DNS.UnexpectedResolutionL
histogram.summary: In some cases, such as when content arrives with embedded references to other servers, or when a page (such as one in SSL) preclude scanning and prefetching, the prefetch system can't (or doesn't) attempt to pre-resolve the hostnames. As an example, a visit to www.cnn.com will fetch content with references to about 12 additional hostnames, none of which might be anticipated. Similarly, clicking on a link in an SSL page won't be anticipated (since scanning in not allowed by default). Such resolutions are termed "Unexpected Resolutions," and the durations associated with those navigation induced DNS resolutions are shown below. If a referring URL is available for the navigation, the relationship to the referring URL was recorded, and future navigations to the referring hostname would have induced a pre-resolution of hostname that caused an entry below. Such any entry may facilitate future listing in the ReferredPositiveHit histogram.

histogram.name: Enterprise.DMToken

histogram.name: Enterprise.Enrollment

histogram.name: Enterprise.ONC.PolicyValidation
histogram.summary: Result of the OpenNetworkConfiguration policy validation.

histogram.name: Enterprise.Policies
histogram.summary: A set of enterprise policy rules that are in use. This is recorded every 24 hours and at startup, if the last recording was earlier than a day before.

histogram.name: Enterprise.Policy
histogram.summary: Events related to fetching, saving and loading user policies, and also device policies on ChromeOS.

histogram.name: Enterprise.PolicyInvalidations
histogram.summary: Events for counting policy invalidations received with and without payloads. Invalidations indicate that a policy has been updated and should be refreshed. Payloads provide context about the policy update, but may be absent if dropped by the invalidation service.

histogram.name: Enterprise.PolicyInvalidationsStartupTime
histogram.summary: Time since startup of the cloud policy code until the policy invalidation service first reported its online status.

histogram.name: Enterprise.PolicyLoadStatus
histogram.summary: Load status from the policy loaders which pull policy settings from the underlying platform, such as Windows Group Policy.

histogram.name: Enterprise.PolicyRefresh

histogram.name: Extensions.ResourceDirectoryTimestampQueryLatency
histogram.summary: The initialization latency (in milliseconds) introduced to each extension resource request by querying the directory timestamp.

histogram.name: Extensions.ResourceLastModifiedDelta
histogram.summary: The difference in seconds between an extension resource's last modification time and its extension base directory's creation time. Recorded on each extension resource request if the difference is non-negative (i.e., the resource's last modification time is more recent than the directory's creation time.) For cases where the directory creation date is more recent, see Extensions.ResourceLastModifiedNegativeDelta instead.

histogram.name: Extensions.ResourceLastModifiedNegativeDelta
histogram.summary: The absolute difference in seconds between an extension resource's last modification time and extension base directory's creation time. Recorded on each extension resource request if the difference is negative (i.e., the directory's creation time is more recent than the resource's last modification time.) For cases where the resource modification time is more recent, see Extensions.ResourceLastModifiedDelta instead.

histogram.summary: Size of the recovered Favicons database relative to the original corrupt database. Recovery is VACUUM-like, so the resulting database should always be smaller. Substantial 100% results would indicate empty databases being recovered, substantial low% results would indicate very little data being recovered.

histogram.name: History.TopSitesRecoveredPercentage
histogram.summary: Size of the recovered TopSites database relative to the original corrupt database. Recovery is VACUUM-like, so the resulting database should always be smaller. Substantial 100% results would indicate empty databases being recovered, substantial low% results would indicate very little data being recovered.

histogram.name: History.TopSitesRecoveredRowsThumbnails

histogram.name: History.TopSitesRecovery
histogram.summary: The TopSites recovery code is written conservatively, with successful recovery committed and any failure leading to rollback. This tracks the outcomes to determine which cases are high-frequency enough to warrant adding additional code to handle them (versus simply deleting the data).

histogram.name: History.TopSitesVisitsByRank

histogram.name: HistoryPage.ClickPositionSubset

histogram.name: HistoryPage.RemoveEntryPosition

histogram.name: HistoryPage.RemoveEntryPositionSubset
histogram.summary: Subset of Remove Entry Position histogram. Contains only the first smaller subset of entries on the page. Number of entries that the deleted entry is older than in History page. Last bucket is any entry of that value or higher. Confirmed removal is not guaranteed, just an initiation of 'Remove selected items'.

histogram.name: Installer.AttemptsCount.Total
histogram.summary: The number of update attempts until the update has been applied. This is reported every time the device has completed an update.

histogram.name: Installer.DevModeErrorCodes
histogram.summary: Errors from update_engine process when running in dev mode.

histogram.name: Installer.DownloadOverheadPercentage
histogram.summary: The overhead in downloading extra bytes due to errors/interruptions. Expressed as a percentage of the bytes that are actually needed to be downloaded for the update to be successful.

histogram.name: Installer.DownloadSourcesUsed
histogram.summary: The combinations of protocol and source server that were used to complete a successful update.

histogram.name: Installer.FullPayloadAttemptNumber
histogram.summary: The number of update attempts with a full update payload until the update has been applied. This is reported on every update attempt.

histogram.name: Installer.NormalErrorCodes
histogram.summary: Errors from update_engine process when running in normal mode.

histogram.name: Installer.OSAgeDays
histogram.summary: The age of the OS, defined as the age of the /etc/lsb-release file. This is reported on every update check but at most once a day.

histogram.name: Installer.PayloadAttemptNumber
histogram.summary: The number of update attempts until the update has been applied. This is reported on every update attempt.

histogram.name: Installer.PayloadFormat
histogram.summary: The type of update payload used to update the device. The difference between "Full" and "Forced Full" is that in the latter, the request sent to Omaha included a directive saying that a delta payload wasn't accepted. A "Full" payload is one where a delta payload was accepted but Omaha provided a full payload. This is reported every time the device has completed an update.

histogram.name: Installer.RebootToNewPartitionAttempt
histogram.summary: The number of consecutive times a device has failed to boot an update that successfully applied. This metric is reported every time the firmware fails to boot the slot with the update and fell back to the slot it originally updated from.

histogram.name: Installer.SuccessfulMBsDownloadedFrom
histogram.summary: Number of MBs downloaded from during an update that completed successfully.

histogram.name: Installer.TimeToRebootMinutes
histogram.summary: Wall-clock duration between when an update has successfully completed (and the user is presented with the "reboot arrow") and when the system has booted into the new update. This is reported every time the device is rebooted after an update has been applied.

histogram.name: Installer.TotalMBsDownloadedFrom
histogram.summary: Total number of MBs downloaded since the last successful update. This also includes all the bytes downloaded during any prior failed attempts.

histogram.name: Installer.UpdateDurationMinutes
histogram.summary: Absolute wall-clock time duration it took for the update to complete from the time an update first began. It includes not just the time the device was up, but also includes the time the device spent sleeping.

histogram.name: Installer.UpdateDurationUptimeMinutes
histogram.summary: Uptime duration it took for the update to complete from the time an update first began. It does not include the time the device spent sleeping, but it does include the uptime spent in waiting for the hourly update checks to happen.

histogram.name: Installer.UpdateNumReboots
histogram.summary: Number of times the device was rebooted by the user since an update began and until it completed successfully.

histogram.name: Installer.UpdatesAbandonedCount
histogram.summary: The number of update attempts that didn't complete because a newer update was detected during the update operation. This is reported every time the device has completed an update.

histogram.name: Installer.UpdatesAbandonedEventCount
histogram.summary: The number of consecutive different abandoned update payloads since the last successful update. This is reported every time an update payload is abandoned because a newer update payload is available.

histogram.name: Installer.UpdateURLSwitches
histogram.summary: Number of times the download URLs were switched due to failures.

histogram.name: Memory.GlyphPagesPerLoad
histogram.summary: The number of glyph pages present in the renderer when it commits a load. Since this is per-sub-process, you can get the average number of glyph pages in the system by multiplying this number with the average number of renderers. Note that this typically won't count the glyph pages added as a result of the load that just committed, since layout will happen after the commit. There are 512 bytes per glyph page, but this number also very closely approximates the number of glyph width map pages in the same renderer. The only difference is that if you have font fallback, it will make a new glyph page and no width page, but in most common cases there is no fallback). Width pages are 1K each (256 floats), so you could think of this value as being the number of "1.5K units related to glyphs per renderer per page load".

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.Chrome
histogram.summary: The swap used by each chrome:// renderer process. Each process provides one sample. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.CompressedDataSize
histogram.summary: The amount of memory that swap was compressed into. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.CompressionRatio
histogram.summary: The ratio of swapped data original size to compressed size. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.Extension
histogram.summary: The swap used by each extension process. Each process provides one sample. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.Gpu
histogram.summary: The swap used by the GPU process. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.HaveSwapped
histogram.summary: Indicates that the system has swapped memory out at least once since boot. Recorded once per UMA ping.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.MemUsedTotal
histogram.summary: The amount of memory that is used by swap, including bookkeeping. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.NativeClient
histogram.summary: The swap used by each Native Client loader process. Each process provides one sample. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.NativeClientBroker
histogram.summary: The swap used by each Native Client broker process. Each process provides one sample. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.NumReads
histogram.summary: The number of reads from swap. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.NumWrites
histogram.summary: The number of writes to swap. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.OriginalDataSize
histogram.summary: The amount of memory that was swapped out. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.PepperPlugin
histogram.summary: The swap used by each Pepper plugin process. Each plugin process provides one sample. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.PepperPluginBroker
histogram.summary: The swap used by each Pepper plugin broker process. Each process provides one sample. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.Plugin
histogram.summary: The swap used by each plugin process. Each plugin process provides one sample. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.Renderer
histogram.summary: The swap used by each renderer process. Each renderer process provides one sample. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.SandboxHelper
histogram.summary: The swap used by each sandbox helper process. Each sandbox helper process provides one sample. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.Total
histogram.summary: The sum of all processes' swap. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.Utility
histogram.summary: The swap used by each utility process. Each utility process provides one sample. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Swap.Worker
histogram.summary: The swap used by each worker process. Each worker process provides one sample. Recorded once per UMA ping if the system has swapped.

histogram.name: Memory.Total
histogram.summary: The sum of all processes. Recorded once per UMA ping.

histogram.name: Memory.Utility
histogram.summary: The private working set used by each utility process. Each utility process provides one sample. Recorded once per UMA ping.

histogram.name: Memory.Worker
histogram.summary: The private working set used by each worker process. Each worker process provides one sample. Recorded once per UMA ping.

histogram.name: Memory.WorkerProcessCount
histogram.summary: TBD.

histogram.name: MemoryAndroid.DeviceMemoryClass
histogram.summary: Value of getMemoryClass() recorded once upon startup. This is an integer, device-specific constant correlated with the amount of memory available on Android device.

histogram.name: MemoryAndroid.EvictionReason
histogram.summary: Reasons behind evictions of individual tabs, recorded upon each tab eviction.

histogram.name: MemoryAndroid.LowMemoryLoadedTabCount
histogram.summary: Number of loaded (memory-resident) tabs when LowMemory notification is delivered.

histogram.name: MemoryAndroid.LowMemoryTimeBetween
histogram.summary: Time between two consecutive LowMemory notification in one foreground session.

histogram.name: MemoryAndroid.NotificationBackground
histogram.summary: Memory notifications delivered through system callbacks to Chrome while in the background.

histogram.name: MemoryAndroid.NotificationForeground
histogram.summary: Memory notifications delivered through system callbacks to Chrome while in the foreground - we count LowMemory notification vs particular levels of TrimMemory foreground notification.

histogram.name: Mist.SwitchResult
histogram.summary: The result (e.g. success or the type of failure) of a modem interface switch operation performed by mist on Chrome OS.

histogram.name: Mouse.PointerSensitivity.Changed
histogram.summary: Tracks mouse sensitivity setting changes by the user. This replaces the old Mouse.Sensitivity.Changed metric.

histogram.name: Mouse.PointerSensitivity.Started
histogram.summary: Tracks mouse sensitivity setting on startup. This replaces the old Mouse.Sensitivity.Started metric.

histogram.name: Mouse.Sensitivity.Changed
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 6/2013, replaced by Mouse.PointerSensitivity.Changed.
histogram.summary: Tracks mouse sensitivity setting.

histogram.name: Mouse.Sensitivity.Started
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 6/2013, replaced by Mouse.PointerSensitivity.Started.
histogram.summary: Tracks mouse sensitivity setting on startup.

histogram.name: MouseEventPrefetch.MouseDownDuration_Click
histogram.summary: Measures the time elapsed between when the user mousedown-ed a link and when the user clicked a link.

histogram.name: MouseEventPrefetch.MouseDownFollowedByClick
histogram.summary: For each click handled by an HTML anchor tag link, whether Blink saw a mousedown event preceding it. This is only measured for clicks handled by the anchor tag's default click event handler.

histogram.name: MouseEventPrefetch.MouseDowns
histogram.summary: The number of mousedown events detected at HTML anchor-tag links' default event handler.

histogram.name: MouseEventPrefetch.MouseOverDuration_Click
histogram.summary: Measures the time elapsed between when the user mouseover-ed a link and when the user clicked a link.

histogram.name: MouseEventPrefetch.MouseOverDuration_NoClick
histogram.summary: Measures the time elapsed between when the user mouseover-ed a link and when the user mouseout-ed a link without click.

histogram.name: MouseEventPrefetch.MouseOvers
histogram.summary: The number of mouseover events detected at HTML anchor-tag links' default event handler.

histogram.name: MouseEventPrefetch.PreTapEventsFollowedByClick
histogram.summary: The tap gesture events detected before click at HTML anchor-tag links' default event handler.

histogram.name: MouseEventPrefetch.TapDownDuration_Click
histogram.summary: Measures the time elapsed between when the user tapdown-ed a link and when the user clicked a link.

histogram.name: MouseEventPrefetch.TapDowns
histogram.summary: The number of gesturetapdown events detected at HTML anchor-tag links' default event handler.

histogram.name: MouseEventPrefetch.TapUnconfirmeds
histogram.summary: The number of gesturetapunconfirmed events detected at HTML anchor-tag links' default event handler.

histogram.name: MultiProfile.DiscardedTabsPerUser
histogram.summary: The relation of discarded tabs vs. the amount of simultaneous users. The counts are the number of discards and the buckets are the number of users. Since the count values are absolute numbers, they need to be normalized before use - so divide the counts by the percentage of users found under 'MultiProfile.UsersPerSession'.

histogram.name: MultiProfile.SessionMode
histogram.summary: The session counter for different multi profile modes which gets stored once per session at the beginning of the session.

histogram.name: MultiProfile.SigninUserUIPath
histogram.summary: Count the number of times each UI path is taken for signing into a new account in a ChromeOS multiprofile session. UI paths include the system tray and the user account switcher on the browser frame.

histogram.name: MultiProfile.SwitchActiveUserUIPath
histogram.summary: Count the number of times each UI path is taken for switching the active account in a ChromeOS multiprofile session. UI paths include the system tray and the keyboard shortcut.

histogram.name: MultiProfile.TeleportWindow
histogram.summary: Counts the number of window teleportations when using separated desktop mode.

histogram.name: MultiProfile.TeleportWindowType
histogram.summary: Counts the number of teleported windows by types in separated desktop mode.

histogram.name: MultiProfile.UsersPerSession
histogram.summary: The number of users simultaneously signed into a multiprofile session on ChromeOS. This is recorded whenever a new user logs in.

histogram.name: Navigation.MainFrameScheme
histogram.summary: The scheme of the URL for each main-frame navigation.

histogram.name: Net.AsyncResourceHandler_PendingDataCount
histogram.summary: The count of unacknowledged ResourceMsg_DataReceived messages. This message is sent once per chunk of data read from the network.

histogram.name: Net.AsyncResourceHandler_PendingDataCount_WhenFull
histogram.summary: The count of unacknowledged ResourceMsg_DataReceived messages at the point where we pause network loading.

histogram.name: Net.AsyncResourceHandler_SharedIOBuffer_Alloc
histogram.summary: The size of a SharedIOBuffer allocation.

histogram.name: Net.AsyncResourceHandler_SharedIOBuffer_Used
histogram.summary: The number of bytes copied into a SharedIOBuffer.

histogram.name: Net.AsyncResourceHandler_SharedIOBuffer_UsedPercentage
histogram.summary: The percentage of a SharedIOBuffer allocation that is actually used.

histogram.name: Net.AuthGenerateToken_basic
histogram.summary: The time to generate a Basic HTTP authentication token.

histogram.name: Net.AuthGenerateToken_digest
histogram.summary: The time to generate a Digest HTTP authentication token.

histogram.name: Net.AuthGenerateToken_negotiate
histogram.summary: The time to generate a Negotiate (or SPNEGO) HTTP authentication token.

histogram.name: Net.AuthGenerateToken_ntlm
histogram.summary: The time to generate an NTLM HTTP authentication token.

histogram.name: Net.CertCommonNameFallback
histogram.summary:
Whether the certificate common name was used for matching the hostname, instead of the subjectAlternativeName.
Measures results for all CAs (internal and publicly-trusted).

histogram.name: Net.CertCommonNameFallbackPrivateCA
histogram.summary:
Whether the certificate common name was used for matching the hostname, instead of the subjectAlternativeName.
Measures results ony for internal (non-publicly-trusted) CAs.

histogram.name: Net.CertificatePinSuccess
histogram.obsolete: Renamed to Net.PublicKeyPinSuccess 28 Oct 2011.
histogram.summary: A validated certificate chain may be subject to additional "pinning" requirements on a per-domain basis. This records the fraction of successful matches between a certificate chain and a pin list.

histogram.name: Net.CertVerifier_Job_Latency
histogram.summary: The actual amount of time spent verifying a certificate using the underlying cryptographic APIs. Because parallel verifications for the same certificate may be coalesced, histograms such as Net.SSLCertVerificationTime may be skewed, due to later verifications taking less overall time. This records the overall time spent verifying a single request, regardless of how many parallel requests are being served by the verification.

histogram.name: Net.CoalescePotential
histogram.summary: The number of times we sent N packets, but could have sent N-1 packets.

histogram.name: Net.ComodoDNSExperimentFailureTime
histogram.summary: The amount of time taken before we failed to resolve the Comodo test DNS record. This is an experiment, run in conjuction with Comodo, to test the viability of a DNS based certificate revocation mechanism.

histogram.name: Net.ComodoDNSExperimentSuccessTime
histogram.summary: The amount of time taken to successfully resolve the Comodo test DNS record. This is an experiment, run in conjuction with Comodo, to test the viability of a DNS based certificate revocation mechanism.

histogram.name: Net.Compress.NoProxy.BytesAfterCompression
histogram.summary: The uncompressed number of bytes received per request that was compressed. Only includes requests which did not go through an explicit proxy and did not go over SSL.

histogram.name: Net.Compress.NoProxy.BytesBeforeCompression
histogram.summary: The compressed number of bytes received per request that was compressed. Only includes requests which did not go through an explicit proxy and did not go over SSL.

histogram.name: Net.Compress.NoProxy.ShouldHaveBeenCompressed
histogram.summary: The uncompressed number of bytes received per request that was not compressed but appears to have been compressible. Only includes requests which did not go through an explicit proxy and did not go over SSL.

histogram.name: Net.Compress.Proxy.BytesAfterCompression
histogram.summary: The uncompressed number of bytes received per request that was compressed. Only includes requests sent through a proxy without SSL.

histogram.name: Net.Compress.Proxy.BytesBeforeCompression
histogram.summary: The compressed number of bytes received per request that was compressed. Only includes requests sent through a proxy without SSL.

histogram.name: Net.Compress.Proxy.ShouldHaveBeenCompressed
histogram.summary: The uncompressed number of bytes received per request that was not compressed but appears to have been compressible. Only includes requests sent through a proxy without SSL.

histogram.name: Net.Compress.SSL.BytesAfterCompression
histogram.summary: The uncompressed number of bytes received per request that was compressed. Only includes requests sent over SSL.

histogram.name: Net.Compress.SSL.BytesBeforeCompression
histogram.summary: The compressed number of bytes received per request that was compressed. Only includes requests sent over SSL.

histogram.name: Net.Compress.SSL.ShouldHaveBeenCompressed
histogram.summary: The uncompressed number of bytes received per request that was not compressed but appears to have been compressible. Only includes requests sent over SSL.

histogram.name: Net.ConnectionTypeCount
histogram.obsolete: The count was inaccurate (it counted transactions rather than connections)
histogram.summary: Each bucket is the number of connections of a particular type that the user has had during the session.

histogram.name: Net.ConnectionTypeCount2
histogram.obsolete: Renamed to match HadConnectionType.
histogram.summary: Each bucket is the number of successful connections of a particular type that the user has had during the session.

histogram.name: Net.ConnectionTypeCount3
histogram.summary: Each bucket is the number of successful connections of a particular type that the user has had during the session.

histogram.name: Net.ConnectionTypeFailCount2
histogram.obsolete: No longer collected.
histogram.summary: Each bucket is the number of failed connections of a particular type that the user has had during the session.

histogram.name: Net.ConnectionUsedSSLv3Fallback
histogram.obsolete: Replaced by Net.ConnectionUsedSSLVersionFallback in Chrome 21.
histogram.summary: True if the HTTP request was to a server which requires SSLv3 fallback

histogram.name: Net.ConnectionUsedSSLVersionFallback
histogram.summary: Nonzero if the HTTP request was to a server which requires SSL version fallback. The value indicates the SSL version the request fell back on.

histogram.name: net.CookieBackingStoreUpdateResults
histogram.obsolete: Initial typo; only here to get results from builds before r59117. See "Cookie." group.
histogram.summary: Whether or not updates to the backing store succeeded or failed, recorded every update.

histogram.name: net.CookieBetweenAccessIntervalMinutes
histogram.obsolete: Initial typo; only here to get results from builds before r59117. See "Cookie." group.
histogram.summary: Intervals between access time updates for each cookie.

histogram.name: net.CookieCount
histogram.obsolete: Initial typo; only here to get results from builds before r59117. See "Cookie." group.
histogram.summary: Number of cookies in the store (recorded every 10 minutes of active browsing time)

histogram.name: net.CookieDeletionCause
histogram.obsolete: Initial typo; only here to get results from builds before r59117. See "Cookie." group.
histogram.summary: For each cookie removed from the store, the reason it was removed.

histogram.name: net.CookieDomainCount
histogram.obsolete: Initial typo; only here to get results from builds before r59117. See "Cookie." group.
histogram.summary: For each domain, number of cookies in that domain (recorded every 10 minutes of active browsing time).

histogram.name: net.CookieDomainPerEtldp1Count
histogram.summary: For every top level domain, number of subdomains in that top level domain (recorded every 10 minutes of active browsing time).

histogram.name: net.CookieEtldp1Count
histogram.obsolete: Initial typo; only here to get results from builds before r59117. See "Cookie." group.
histogram.summary: For every top level domain, number of cookies in that domain (recorded every 10 minutes of active browsing time).

histogram.name: net.CookieEvictedLastAccessMinutes
histogram.obsolete: Initial typo; only here to get results from builds before r59117. See "Cookie." group.
histogram.summary: For each evicted (not expired) cookie, the amount of time since it was last used

histogram.name: net.CookieExpirationDurationMinutes
histogram.obsolete: Initial typo; only here to get results from builds before r59117. See "Cookie." group.
histogram.summary: Number of minutes until cookie expires when set.

histogram.name: net.CookieTimeGet
histogram.obsolete: Initial typo; only here to get results from builds before r59117. See "Cookie." group.
histogram.summary: The amount of time (ms) to get cookies for each URL request.

histogram.name: net.CookieTimeLoad
histogram.obsolete: Initial typo; only here to get results from builds before r59117. See "Cookie." group.
histogram.summary: The amount of time (ms) to load the persistent cookie store at browser start.

histogram.name: Net.CountOfAlternateProtocolServers
histogram.summary: The total number of severs to which alternative protocol was used. This counts the number of servers persisted to prefs file.

histogram.name: Net.CountOfPipelineCapableServers
histogram.summary: The total number of severs that support HTTP pipelining. This counts the number of servers persisted to prefs file.

histogram.name: Net.CountOfSpdyServers
histogram.summary: The total number of SPDY server names persisted to prefs file.

histogram.name: Net.CountOfSpdySettings
histogram.summary: The total number of SPDY Settings properties persisted to prefs file.

histogram.name: Net.CRLRequestFailedTimeMs
histogram.summary: When validating an HTTPS certificate we may have to block to fetch one or more revocation lists. This measures the amount of time that failures to get CRL information take.

histogram.name: Net.CRLRequestSuccess
histogram.summary: When validating an HTTPS certificate we may have to block to fetch one or more revocation lists. This records the fraction of successful requests.

histogram.name: Net.CRLRequestTimeMs
histogram.summary: When validating an HTTPS certificate we may have to block to fetch one or more revocation lists. This measures the amount of time that each fetch takes.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentLength
histogram.summary: The total content size in KB of all HTTP/HTTPS response bodies in the previous calendar day. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentLength_DataReductionProxyEnabled
histogram.summary: The total content size in KB of all HTTP/HTTPS response bodies in the previous calendar day while the data reduction proxy setting was enabled. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentLength_DataReductionProxyEnabled_Https
histogram.summary: The total content size in KB of all HTTPS response bodies in the previous calendar day while the data reduction proxy setting was enabled. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentLength_DataReductionProxyEnabled_LongBypass
histogram.summary: The total content size in KB of all long-bypassed HTTP response bodies in the previous calendar day while the data reduction proxy setting was enabled. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentLength_DataReductionProxyEnabled_ShortBypass
histogram.summary: The total content size in KB of all short-bypassed HTTP response bodies in the previous calendar day while the data reduction proxy setting was enabled. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentLength_DataReductionProxyEnabled_Unknown
histogram.summary: The total content size in KB of all HTTP response bodies for requests that were not served by the enabled data reduction proxy for unknown reasons in the previous calendar day while the data reduction proxy setting was enabled. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentLength_ViaDataReductionProxy
histogram.summary: The total content size in KB of all HTTP/HTTPS response bodies in the previous calendar day via the data reduction proxy. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentPercent_DataReductionProxyEnabled
histogram.summary: The percentage of total HTTP/HTTPS response body size while the data reduction proxy is enabled to total HTTP/HTTPS response body size in the previous calendar day. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentPercent_DataReductionProxyEnabled_Https
histogram.summary: The percentage of total HTTPS response body size while the data reduction proxy is enabled to total HTTP/HTTPS response body size in the previous calendar day. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentPercent_DataReductionProxyEnabled_LongBypass
histogram.summary: The percentage of total long-bypassed response body size while the data reduction proxy is enabled to total HTTP/HTTPS response body size in the previous calendar day. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentPercent_DataReductionProxyEnabled_ShortBypass
histogram.summary: The percentage of total short-bypassed response body size while the data reduction proxy is enabled to total HTTP/HTTPS response body size in the previous calendar day. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentPercent_DataReductionProxyEnabled_Unknown
histogram.summary: The percentage of total body size of responses that were not served by the data reduction proxy for unknown reason while the data reduction proxy is enabled to total HTTP/HTTPS response body size in the previous calendar day. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentPercent_ViaDataReductionProxy
histogram.summary: The percentage of total HTTP/HTTPS response body size via the data reduction proxy to total HTTP/HTTPS response body size in the previous calendar day. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentSavingPercent
histogram.summary: The percentage of data saving in the previous calendar day. A negative saving will be shown as zero. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentSavingPercent_DataReductionProxyEnabled
histogram.summary: The percentage of data saving in the previous calendar day while the data reduction proxy was enabled. A negative saving will be shown as zero. This only counts responses while the data reduction proxy is enabled. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyContentSavingPercent_ViaDataReductionProxy
histogram.summary: The percentage of data saving in the previous calendar day via the data reduction proxy. A negative saving will be shown as zero. This only counts responses via the data reduction proxy. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyHttpContentLengthViaDataReductionProxy
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated- see Net.DailyContentLength_ViaDataReductionProxy.
histogram.summary: Total size in KB of all response bodies in the previous calendar day that were received through the data reduction proxy.

histogram.name: Net.DailyHttpContentLengthWithDataReductionProxyEnabled
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated- see Net.DailyContentLength_DataReductionProxyEnabled
histogram.summary: Total size in KB of all response bodies in the previous calendar day that were received when the data reduction proxy was enabled.

histogram.name: Net.DailyHttpContentSavings
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated- see Net.DailyContentSavingPercent.
histogram.summary: The percentage of data saving in the previous calendar day. A negative saving will be shown as zero.

histogram.name: Net.DailyHttpContentSavings_DataReductionProxy
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated- see Net.DailyContentSavingPercent_DataReductionProxyEnabled.
histogram.summary: The percentage of data saving in the previous calendar day when the data reduction proxy was enabled for at least some responses during the day. A negative saving will be shown as zero.

histogram.name: Net.DailyHttpOriginalContentLength
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated- see Net.DailyOriginalContentLength.
histogram.summary: Total size in KB specified in the X-Original-Content-Length headers of all responses in the previous calendar day. If the header is not present in a response, the size of the response body is used.

histogram.name: Net.DailyHttpReceivedContentLength
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated- see Net.DailyContentLength.
histogram.summary: Total size in KB of all response bodies in the previous calendar day.

histogram.name: Net.DailyOriginalContentLength
histogram.summary: The total size in KB specified in the X-Original-Content-Length headers of all HTTP/HTTPS response bodies in the previous calendar day. If the header is not present in a response, the size of the response body is used. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyOriginalContentLength_DataReductionProxyEnabled
histogram.summary: The total size in KB specified in the X-Original-Content-Length headers of all HTTP/HTTPS response bodies in the previous calendar day while the data reduction proxy is enabled. If the header is not present in a response, the size of the response body is used. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyOriginalContentLength_ViaDataReductionProxy
histogram.summary: The total size in KB specified in the X-Original-Content-Length headers of all HTTP/HTTPS response bodies in the previous calendar day via the data reduction proxy. If the header is not present in a response, the size of the response body is used. The metric is reported when the first response in the current day is received.

histogram.name: Net.DailyReceivedContentViaDataReductionProxy
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated- see Net.DailyContentPercent_ViaDataReductionProxy.
histogram.summary: The percentage of Net.DailyHttpContentLengthViaDataReductionProxy in Net.DailyHttpReceivedContentLength.

histogram.name: Net.DailyReceivedContentWithDataReductionProxyEnabled
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated- see Net.DailyContentPercent_DataReductionProxyEnabled.
histogram.summary: The percentage of Net.DailyHttpContentLengthWithDataReductionProxyEnabled in Net.DailyHttpReceivedContentLength.

histogram.name: Net.DhcpWpadCancelTime
histogram.summary: Measures time from initiating a fetch of a PAC file from DHCP WPAD to cancellation of the fetch. For a given fetch, only one of the cancellation or completion histograms will be added to.

histogram.name: Net.DhcpWpadCompletionTime
histogram.summary: Measures time from initiating a fetch of a PAC file from DHCP WPAD to completion of the fetch. For a given fetch, only one of the cancellation or completion histograms will be added to.

histogram.name: Net.DhcpWpadFetchError
histogram.summary: Tracks the net error codes received when the DHCP WPAD fetch fails to retrieve a PAC file (including PAC_NOT_IN_DHCP, which is not really an error but an indication that a PAC URL was not configured in DHCP).

histogram.name: Net.DhcpWpadGetAdaptersAddressesError
histogram.summary: Tracks the frequency of each of the different known error codes of calling the GetAdaptersAddresses Win32 API.

histogram.name: Net.DhcpWpadGetAdaptersAddressesTime
histogram.summary: Measures the time taken to call the GetAdaptersAddresses Win32 API, to validate our understanding that it should complete quickly enough to call synchronously from the network thread.

histogram.name: Net.DhcpWpadNumAdaptersAtWaitTimer
histogram.summary: Total number of adapters enabled for DHCP as seen when the wait timer in the DHCP WPAD code hits. This timer fires after a timeout from when we get some information from the first adapter to finish.

histogram.name: Net.DhcpWpadNumPendingAdaptersAtWaitTimer
histogram.summary: Number of adapters enabled for DHCP that we have not completed retrieving information for, as seen when the wait timer in the DHCP WPAD code hits. This timer fires after a timeout from when we get some information from the first adapter to finish.

histogram.name: Net.DhcpWpadUnhandledDhcpError
histogram.summary: Counts the number of errors from the DhcpRequestParams API that we do not have specific handling for, so that we can see if there is an abnormally high rate.

histogram.name: Net.DNS_Resolution_And_TCP_Connection_Latency
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated- see Net.DNS_Resolution_And_TCP_Connection_Latency2

histogram.name: Net.Dns_Resolution_And_TCP_Connection_Latency
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated- see Net.DNS_Resolution_And_TCP_Connection_Latency2

histogram.name: Net.DNS_Resolution_And_TCP_Connection_Latency2
histogram.summary: The time measured before starting DNS lookup until after the connection is complete.

histogram.name: Net.Dns_Resolution_And_TCP_Connection_Latency2
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated- see Net.DNS_Resolution_And_TCP_Connection_Latency2

histogram.name: Net.DoubleGetExperiment_InitialResponseMethod
histogram.summary: The number of HTTP request responses with MS Office Docs MIME types. The responses are classified based on their method type and cacheability (POST, cacheable GET and non-cacheable GET). The histogram is used in Double GET Experiment, where successful non-cacheable GET requests are intercepted after initial response and repeated in order to determine how much reissuing non-cacheable GET requests influences their error rate. The histogram tracks only initial requests (not the repeated ones).

histogram.name: Net.DoubleGetExperiment_ResponseCode
histogram.summary: The response codes encountered for GET request repeated in Double GET Experiment. In the experiment successful non-cacheable GET requests are intercepted after initial response and repeated. The goal of the experiment is to measure how much reissuing non-cacheable GET requests influences their error rate.

histogram.name: Net.DownloadBandwidth
histogram.summary: Kbps on download streams exceeding 25KB. Measures from the beginning of the first byte received until the end of flowing data.

histogram.name: Net.ErrorCodesForImages

histogram.name: Net.ErrorCodesForMainFrame
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 2011/5/24, replaced by Net.ErrorCodesForMainFrame2, which measures the same data but uses a different bucket structure (adds guard buckets).

histogram.name: Net.ErrorCodesForMainFrame2
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 2012/5/16, replaced by Net.ErrorCodesForMainFrame3, which measures the same data but includes ERR_ABORTED and OK.
histogram.summary: Positive net error code that a page failed with. Note that this only counts the errors in "main frames", so it is a measure of the error pages that users actually see (it does not for example count the error codes for subresoures on a page).

histogram.name: Net.ErrorCodesForMainFrame3
histogram.summary: Positive net error codes that requests for pages end with, including net::OK and net::ERR_ABORTED. This only counts loads in "main frames" (it does not for example count the error codes for subresoures on a page).

histogram.name: Net.ErrorCodesForSubresources

histogram.name: Net.ErrorCodesForSubresources2
