histogram.name: Net.FtpDataConnectionErrorCount
histogram.summary: The number of times each FTP Error was observed.

histogram.name: Net.FtpDataConnectionErrorHappened
histogram.summary: The number of Chrome sessions which encountered the indicates FTP Error. This prevents allowing a user that retried a connection many times (getting an error each time) from biasing the tallies.

histogram.name: Net.FtpServerTypeCount
histogram.summary: Each bucket is the number of FTP server types the user has encountered during the session.

histogram.name: Net.GetProxyForUrl_FAIL
histogram.summary: The time spent waiting for WinHttpGetProxyForUrl to return with error.

histogram.name: Net.GetProxyForUrl_OK
histogram.summary: The time spent waiting for WinHttpGetProxyForUrl to return with success.

histogram.name: Net.GoogleConnectionUsedSSLVersionFallback
histogram.summary: Nonzero if the HTTP request was to a Google server which required SSL version fallback. The value indicates the SSL version the request fell back on. Since Google servers support TLS 1.2, any fallback is an indication of network middleware problems.

histogram.name: Net.HadConnectionType
histogram.obsolete: The count was inaccurate (it counted transactions rather than connections).
histogram.summary: Each bucket is a boolean (0 or 1) indicating whether the user has had a connection of that type during the session.

histogram.name: Net.HadConnectionType2
histogram.obsolete: This statistic measures successful and failed connections, the new one only measures successful ones.
histogram.summary: Each bucket is a boolean (0 or 1) indicating whether the user has had a connection of that type during the session.

histogram.name: Net.HadConnectionType3
histogram.summary: Each bucket is a boolean (0 or 1) indicating whether the user has had a successful connection of that type during the session.

histogram.name: Net.HadFtpServerType
histogram.summary: Each bucket is a boolean (0 or 1) indicating whether the user has had a connection with an FTP server of that type during the session.

histogram.name: Net.HttpAuthCount
histogram.summary: Per-authentication-scheme counts of authentication attempts and rejections.

histogram.name: Net.HttpAuthResource
histogram.summary: Count of authentication requests for top level pages vs. sub-resources, such as images or iframes.

histogram.name: Net.HttpAuthTarget
histogram.summary: Per-authentication-scheme counts of authentication targets, such as secure servers or proxies.

histogram.name: Net.HttpConnectionLatency
histogram.summary: Time between the HttpNetworkTransaction requesting a connection and the time it connected.

histogram.name: Net.HttpContentFreshnessLifetime
histogram.summary: Length of time that a received resource will be cacheable.

histogram.name: Net.HttpContentLength
histogram.summary: Size of the response body. This is the actual number of bytes received, which usually agrees with but is not necessarily the same as the size specified by the Content-Length header.

histogram.name: Net.HttpContentLengthCacheable
histogram.summary: Size of the response body if it is cacheable. This is the actual number of bytes received, which usually agrees with but is not necessarily the same as the size specified by the Content-Length header.

histogram.name: Net.HttpContentLengthCacheable24Hours
histogram.summary: Size of the response body if it is cacheable for at least 24 hours. This is the actual number of bytes received, which usually agrees with but is not necessarily the same as the size specified by the Content-Length header.

histogram.name: Net.HttpContentLengthCacheable4Hours
histogram.summary: Size of the response body if it is cacheable for at least 4 hours. This is the actual number of bytes received, which usually agrees with but is not necessarily the same as the size specified by the Content-Length header.

histogram.name: Net.HttpContentLengthDifference
histogram.summary: The difference between the size specified in the X-Original-Content-Length header and the size of teh response body. This is zero if the X-Original-Content-Length header is not present in the response.

histogram.name: Net.HttpContentLengthDifferenceWithValidOCL
histogram.summary: The difference between the size specified in the X-Original-Content-Length header and the size of the response body. Only includes resources that have the X-Original-Content-Length header.

histogram.name: Net.HttpContentLengthWithValidOCL
histogram.summary: Size of the response body. Only includes resources that have the X-Original-Content-Length header.

histogram.name: Net.HttpJob.TotalTime
histogram.summary: Time it takes to complete an HttpJob, from starting the transaction until we are done reading.

histogram.name: Net.HttpJob.TotalTimeCached
histogram.summary: Time it takes to complete an HttpJob, from starting the transaction until we are done reading, for jobs served from the cache.

histogram.name: Net.HttpJob.TotalTimeCancel
histogram.summary: Time it takes to complete an HttpJob, from starting the transaction until the job is killed. Note that we didn't detect the end of the data for this job.

histogram.name: Net.HttpJob.TotalTimeNotCached
histogram.summary: Time it takes to complete an HttpJob, from starting the transaction until we are done reading, for jobs not served from the cache.

histogram.name: Net.HttpJob.TotalTimeSuccess
histogram.summary: Time it takes to complete an HttpJob, from starting the transaction until we are done reading, for jobs when we read until no more data is available.

histogram.name: Net.HttpOriginalContentLength
histogram.summary: Size specified in the X-Original-Content-Length header. If this header is not present in the response, the size of the response body is used.

histogram.name: Net.HttpOriginalContentLengthWithValidOCL
histogram.summary: Size specified in the X-Original-Content-Length header. Only includes resources that have the X-Original-Content-Length header.

histogram.name: Net.HttpProxySocketRequestTime
histogram.summary: Time it takes to request a new (unused) HTTP proxy socket.

histogram.name: Net.HttpResponseCode
histogram.summary: The count of HTTP Response codes encountered.

histogram.name: Net.HttpResponseCode_Nxx_MainFrame
histogram.summary: The count of HTTP Response codes encountered, in response to MAIN_FRAME requests only; saving only the hundreds digit, e.g. 100->1, 300->3.

histogram.name: Net.HttpSocketType
histogram.summary: The counts of the type of sockets (all HTTP sockets, regardless of any proxy used) used for HTTP[s].

histogram.name: Net.HttpTimeToFirstByte
histogram.summary: Time from when an HTTP request is issued to when the first byte is processed.

histogram.name: Net.IOError_SocketReuseType
histogram.summary: The count of handleable socket errors (connection abort/close/reset) per socket reuse type.

histogram.name: Net.IOError_SocketReuseType_disable_late_binding
histogram.obsolete: Late bindings are on by default now.
histogram.summary: The count of handleable socket errors (connection abort/close/reset) per socket reuse type. Socket late binding is disabled.

histogram.name: Net.IOError_SocketReuseType_enable_late_binding
histogram.obsolete: Late bindings are on by default now.
histogram.summary: The count of handleable socket errors (connection abort/close/reset) per socket reuse type. Socket late binding is enabled.

histogram.name: Net.IPv6ConnectDuration
histogram.summary: Duration of time spent during the UDP-connect IPv6 probe.

histogram.name: Net.IPv6ConnectFailureMatch
histogram.summary: Whether the the interface-enumeration IPv6 probe method failed given that the UDP-connect IPV6 probe failed.

histogram.name: Net.IPv6ConnectSuccessMatch
histogram.summary: Whether the the interface-enumeration IPv6 probe method was successful given that the UDP-connect IPV6 probe was successful.

histogram.name: Net.IPv6Status
histogram.summary: The probe results when a test for IPv6 support is done.

histogram.name: Net.IPv6Status_retest
histogram.summary: The probe results when a test for IPv6 support is done, after a network change event.

histogram.name: Net.MTPR_GetProxyForUrl_Thread_Wait_Time
histogram.summary: The time that a (non-cancelled) proxy resolution request was stalled waiting for an execution thread, for MultiThreadedProxyResolver.

histogram.name: Net.MTPR_GetProxyForUrl_Time
histogram.summary: The total time that it took for a (non-cancelled) proxy resolution request to complete, for MultiThreadedProxyResolver.

histogram.name: Net.NetworkErrorsRecovered.MainFrame
histogram.summary: How often automatically retrying to download the main frame of a page in response to specific HTTP network errors succeeds.

histogram.name: Net.NetworkErrorsRecovered.Subresource
histogram.summary: How often automatically retrying to download a subresource in response to specific HTTP network errors succeeds.

histogram.name: Net.NetworkErrorsUnrecovered.MainFrame
histogram.summary: How often automatically retrying to download the main frame of a page in response to specific HTTP network errors returns another network error. Histogram includes only the error code that triggered the retry.

histogram.name: Net.NetworkErrorsUnrecovered.Subresource
histogram.summary: How often automatically retrying to download a subresource in response to specific HTTP network errors returns another network error. Histogram includes only the error code that triggered the retry.

histogram.name: Net.NotifyAddrChangeFailures
histogram.summary: On Windows, NetworkChangeNotifierWin calls NotifyAddrChange, which can fail for unknown reasons. This records the number of times it fails in a row before a successful call. If it never succeeds, or takes over 100 tries, a value of 100 is recorded. See http://crbug.com/69198

histogram.name: Net.NumDuplicateCookiesInDb
histogram.summary: The number of duplicate cookies that were present in the cookie store during startup.

histogram.name: Net.OCSPRequestFailedTimeMs
histogram.summary: When validating an HTTPS certificate we may have to make one or more HTTP fetches to OCSP responders in order to get revocation information. This measures the amount of time that failures to get OCSP information take.

histogram.name: Net.OCSPRequestSuccess
histogram.summary: When validating an HTTPS certificate we may have to make one or more HTTP fetches to OCSP responders in order to get revocation information. This records the fraction of successful requests.

histogram.name: Net.OCSPRequestTimeMs
histogram.summary: When validating an HTTPS certificate we may have to make one or more HTTP fetches to OCSP responders in order to get revocation information. This measures the amount of time that each of those requests takes.

histogram.name: Net.OSErrorsForGetAddrinfo
histogram.summary: Positive error code that was returned by the system library "getaddrinfo()". This error code is platform specific, so when there is a Windows/Linux conflict, both decodings are shown.

histogram.name: Net.OSErrorsForGetAddrinfo_Linux
histogram.summary: Positive error code that was returned by the system library "getaddrinfo()".

histogram.name: Net.OSErrorsForGetAddrinfo_Mac
histogram.summary: Positive error code that was returned by the system library "getaddrinfo()".

histogram.name: Net.OSErrorsForGetAddrinfo_Win
histogram.summary: Positive error code that was returned by the system library "getaddrinfo()".

histogram.name: Net.PreconnectedLinkNavigations
histogram.summary: Indicate whether a link navigation was preceded by a recent pre-connect trigger (within 10 seconds). There is a high chance that loading the page used a preconnected TCP session.

histogram.name: Net.PreconnectedNavigation
histogram.summary: Indicate whether a URLRequest was preceded by a recent pre-connect trigger (within 10 seconds). There is a high chance that loading the resource used a preconnected TCP session.

histogram.name: Net.PreconnectMotivation
histogram.summary: When a preconnection is made, indicate what the motivation was.
histogram.details: Currently, the most common (only?) motivations are SELF_REFERAL, LEARNED_REFERAL and OMNIBOX. The SELF_REFERAL indicates that we made sure a second connection was available for a resource that either was never before seen, or has historically had no subresources. The LEARNED_REFERAL indicates that we "learned" that a subresource was commonly needed, and that motivated the TCP/IP preconnect. The OMNIBOX motivation happens when a search is being suggested, and we preconnect to the search provider. (WARNING: Prior to version 7.517.*, enums 7, 8, and 9 may be confused, as EARLY_LOAD_MOTIVATED was inserted new 6 value.)

histogram.name: Net.PreconnectProxyStatus
histogram.summary: Indicate whether there was a proxy to preclude preconnection.

histogram.name: Net.PreconnectSubresourceEval
histogram.summary: What did we decide to do about a predicted resource, based on the historical expected number of connection that this subresource will require.
histogram.details: This is basically the current thresholding of the SubresourceExpectation, relative to current static thresholds, and taking into account whether preconnection is enabled (i.e., if preconnection is disabled, we'll never decide to preconnect).

histogram.name: Net.PreconnectSubresourceExpectation
histogram.summary: The expected number of connections, times 100, that we'll make to a given subresource, based on learned history.
histogram.details: By comparing this to thresholds, we decide if we will preconnect, preresolve, or do nothing. This histogram can be used to select those static thresholds.

histogram.name: Net.PreconnectTriggerUsed
histogram.summary: Indicate whether if a preconnect trigger is followed by a resource request (from link navigations) to the host or not. This is to measure precision of link-based preconnect triggers.

histogram.name: Net.PreconnectUtilization
histogram.obsolete: Sourced data corrected, and replaced by NetPreconnectUtilization2
histogram.summary: Indicate final utilization for each attempted socket connection.
histogram.details: We also include stats for non-speculative sockets. Some socket connections may never connect, and others may never be used (as the user may abort before then).

histogram.name: Net.PreconnectUtilization2
histogram.summary: Indicate final utilization for each attempted socket connection.
histogram.details: We also include stats for non-speculative sockets. Some socket connections may never connect, and others may never be used (as the user may abort before then).

histogram.name: Net.Prefetch.Pattern
histogram.summary: The completion status of prefetches that have finished loading.
histogram.details:
Measurement occurs at ResourceLoader::ResponseCompleted so requests canceled before that point are not registered.
Note that "success from cache" means that the UrlRequest::was_cached() was true, and "success from network" means that was_cached() was false. Validated results are considered cached, even though a conditional network request is made.

histogram.name: Net.Prefetch.PrefilterBytesReadFromNetwork
histogram.summary: Number of bytes read from the network on behalf of prefetch requests. This is prefilter, so before any decompression.

histogram.name: Net.Prefetch.TimeBeforeCancel
histogram.summary: Time spent on prefetch requests before the request was canceled.

histogram.name: Net.Prefetch.TimeSpentPrefetchingFromCache
histogram.summary: Time spent on prefetch requests when fetched from cache.

histogram.name: Net.Prefetch.TimeSpentPrefetchingFromNetwork
histogram.summary: Time spent on prefetch requests when fetched from the network, including validation time.

histogram.name: Net.Priority_High_Latency
histogram.obsolete: Replaced by Net.Priority_High_Latency_b.
histogram.summary: Time from the start of the http transaction until the first byte of the response for high priority (currently frame and subframe) requests. Only times under 10 minutes are recorded.

histogram.name: Net.Priority_High_Latency_b
histogram.summary: Time from the start of the http transaction until the first byte of the response for high priority (currently frame and subframe) requests.

histogram.name: Net.Priority_Low_Latency
histogram.obsolete: Replaced by Net.Priority_Low_Latency_b.
histogram.summary: Time from the start of the http transaction until the first byte of the response for low priority (non-frame/subframe) requests. Only times under 10 minutes are recorded.

histogram.name: Net.Priority_Low_Latency_b
histogram.summary: Time from the start of the http transaction until the first byte of the response for low priority (non-frame/subframe) requests.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyPollConfigurationTime
histogram.summary: The time in milliseconds spent fetch the system proxy configuration, when polling it for changes.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.AbandonedExecutionTotalTime
histogram.summary: The total amount of time that was spent executing the proxy script during "tracing" runs (executions of the script which discovered a new DNS dependency and were subsequently abandoned).

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.BlockingDNSMode.AbandonedExecutionTotalTime
histogram.summary: The total amount of time that was spent executing the proxy script during "tracing" runs (executions of the script which discovered a new DNS dependency and were subsequently abandoned).

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.BlockingDNSMode.DnsWaitTotalTime
histogram.summary: The total amount of time that was spent in the non-blocking DNS bindings while executing PAC scripts. This includes the times for abandoned executions.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.BlockingDNSMode.ExecutionTime
histogram.summary: The amount of time inside of V8 that the proxy script spent executing for the final pass. This includes the time spent in the javascript bindings. This does not include the time spent in abandoned execution passes.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.BlockingDNSMode.NumAlerts
histogram.summary: The number of times that alert() was called in the final execution of the script.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.BlockingDNSMode.NumErrors
histogram.summary: The number of errors that were seen in the final execution of the script.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.BlockingDNSMode.NumRestarts
histogram.summary: The number of times that the PAC script execution was restarted.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.BlockingDNSMode.TotalTime
histogram.summary: The total time that the proxy resolution took. This includes all the time spent waiting for DNS, PAC script execution, and restarts.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.BlockingDNSMode.TotalTimeDNS
histogram.summary: The total time that proxy resolution spent waiting for DNS. This also includes any queuing delays on the origin thread waiting for the DNS result to be processed.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.BlockingDNSMode.UniqueDNS
histogram.summary: The number of unique DNS hostnames that the PAC script tried to resolve. The *Ex() versions of the bindings count separately.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.DnsWaitTotalTime
histogram.summary: The total amount of time that was spent in the non-blocking DNS bindings while executing PAC scripts. This includes the times for abandoned executions.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.ExecutionTime
histogram.summary: The amount of time inside of V8 that the proxy script spent executing for the final pass. This includes the time spent in the javascript bindings (which is probably dominated by Net.ProxyResolver.DnsWaitTotalTime). This does not include the time spent in abandoned execution passes.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.NumAlerts
histogram.summary: The number of times that alert() was called in the final execution of the script.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.NumErrors
histogram.summary: The number of errors that were seen in the final execution of the script.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.NumRestarts
histogram.summary: The number of times that the PAC script execution was restarted.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.OriginThreadLatency
histogram.summary: The amount of time it took upon completion to run the final task posted back to the IO thread.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.TotalTime
histogram.summary: The total time that the proxy resolution took. This includes all the time spent waiting for DNS, PAC script execution, and restarts.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.TotalTimeDNS
histogram.summary: The total time that proxy resolution spent waiting for DNS. This also includes any queuing delays on the origin thread waiting for the DNS result to be processed.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.TotalTimeWorkerThread
histogram.summary: The total time that the proxy resolution took, not including the post back to the origin thread. This includes all the time spent waiting for DNS, PAC script execution, and restarts.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.UniqueDNS
histogram.summary: The number of unique DNS hostnames that the PAC script tried to resolve. The *Ex() versions of the bindings count separately.

histogram.name: Net.ProxyResolver.URLSize
histogram.summary: The length of the URL that was passed into the PAC script.

histogram.name: Net.PublicKeyPinFailureDomain

histogram.name: Net.PublicKeyPinSuccess

histogram.name: Net.QuicEphemeralPortsSuggested

histogram.name: NewTabPage.ActionAndroid

histogram.name: NewTabPage.AppsPageDragSource
histogram.summary: Histogram for the source of app page drags. For any succesful drop onto an apps pane of the NTP, this logs where the drag originated.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.BookmarkActionAndroid
histogram.summary: Actions taken by users on partner bookmarks (editing / renaming) on the NTP on Android.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.DefaultPageType
histogram.summary: The default pane when the NTP is first opened.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.HoverTimeClicked
histogram.summary: Histogram of the time, in milliseconds, users have the cursor over a most visited thumbnail before clicking.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.HoverTimeNotClicked
histogram.summary: Histogram of the time, in milliseconds, users have the cursor over a most visited thumbnail before moving it away from the thumbnail without clicking.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.MobilePromo
histogram.summary: Android: Tallies counts for how the user interacted with the NTP promo page.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.MostVisited
histogram.summary: Histogram for user clicks of the most visited thumbnails. The value is equal to the index of the thumbnail.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.MostVisitedAction
histogram.summary: Action taken by the user on the Most Visited NTP pane. If the user switches panes during this use of the NTP, this action is sometimes not recorded. Ask mpearson@ for details.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.MostVisitedTilePlacementExperiment
histogram.summary: Records anomalous events for the Most Visited Tile Placement experiment, where it is unable to operate as expected. These are recorded during New Tab Page load time, once for every NTP.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.NonVisibleScreenshots
histogram.summary: The number of screenshots that were cached for the non-visible but ranked suggestions on the Suggested NTP pane.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.NonVisibleSuggestedSiteRank
histogram.summary: Given that the user has typed a URL, and given that that specific URL was ranked but not visible on the Suggested pane of the NTP, this is the rank that the Suggested pane had for that URL.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.NumberOfExternalTiles
histogram.summary: The number of external tiles that are displayed on the NTP. External tiles are those for which the visuals are handled by the page itself, not by the iframe. Recorded before changing focus away from the NTP, be it by navigating to a URL, switching tabs, changing the active window or closing the tab/shutting down Chrome.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.NumberOfMouseOvers
histogram.summary: The total number of times the user hovered the mouse over Most Visited tile or title elements before changing focus away from the NTP, be it by navigating to a URL, switching tabs, changing the active window or closing the tab/shutting down Chrome.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.OtherSessionsMenu
histogram.summary: Histogram for usage of the menu on the NTP that allows the user to access tabs from other devices.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.PreviousSelectedPageType
histogram.summary: The pane that had been previously selected when the user switches panes in the NTP.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.Promo.Bubble
histogram.summary: Histogram for NTP bubble promo activity.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.Promo.Notification
histogram.summary: Histogram for NTP notification promo activity.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.SearchURLs.Total
histogram.summary: TBD.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.SelectedPageType
histogram.summary: The pane selected when the user switches panes in the NTP.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.SessionRestore
histogram.summary: Histogram for user clicks of the Recently Closed items. The value is the recency of the entry being restored (0 is most recent).

histogram.name: NewTabPage.SingleSessionPageSwitches
histogram.summary: Histogram to track how many times a user switched pages in a single NTP session.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.SuggestedSite
histogram.summary: Histogram for user clicks of the suggested site thumbnails. The value is equal to the index of the thumbnail.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.SuggestedSitesAction
histogram.summary: Action taken by the user on the Suggested Sites NTP pane.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.SuggestedSitesLoadTime
histogram.summary: Time to load the Suggested Sites NTP pane, in milliseconds.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.SuggestedSitesViewTime
histogram.summary: Time spent on the Suggested Sites NTP pane, in seconds.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.SuggestionsImpression
histogram.summary: Histogram for impressions on the various most visited tiles. The value is equal to the index of the thumbnail.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.SuggestionsType
histogram.summary: Indicate, for each impression of the New Tab Page, whether the suggestions were obtained from the client or server. Recorded before changing focus away from the NTP, be it by navigating to a URL, switching tabs, changing the active window or closing the tab/shutting down Chrome.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.ThumbnailErrorRate
histogram.summary: The percentage of errors per attempts to load image thumbnails on the New Tab Page. When an error occurs, a grey tile is shown instead of a thumbnail image. We measure the rate instead of the number of errors because multiple attempts are made to load images at different times during the NTP's lifetime. Each NTP session's error rate is logged after the user navigates to a new URL from that NTP.

histogram.name: NewTabPage.ThumbnailFallbackRate
histogram.summary: The percentage of times most visited tiles use the fallback thumbnail. Only requests that actually specify a fallback thumbnail are considered here. We measure the rate instead of the number of errors because multiple attempts are made to load thumbnails at different times during the NTP's lifetime. Each NTP session's error rate is logged after the user navigates to a new URL from that NTP.

histogram.name: Overscroll.Completed
histogram.summary: Completed overscroll gestures.
histogram.details: An overscroll gesture starts when user scrolls past the edge of the web page and continues scrolling in the same direction. An overscroll gesture is completed when user stops scrolling (e.g. by lifting the fingers from the touchscreen or touchpad).

histogram.name: Overscroll.Navigated
histogram.summary: Navigations that were triggered due to completed overscroll gesture. Note that not all completed overscroll gestures trigger a navigation.

histogram.name: Overscroll.Started

histogram.name: P2P.Client.Canceled.WaitingTimeSeconds
histogram.summary: The wall-clock time spent until a lookup was canceled. This is reported every time p2p is used to find a candidate but the request was canceled.

histogram.name: P2P.Client.Found.CandidateCount
histogram.summary: The number of candidates on the LAN, i.e. the number of peers on the LAN offering at least N bytes of the requested file X. This is reported after examining responses from all peers on the LAN and picking a candidate.

histogram.name: P2P.Client.Found.ConnectionCount
histogram.summary: The number of p2p downloads of the peer that the returned URL points to. This is reported after examining responses from all peers on the LAN and picking a candidate.

histogram.name: P2P.Client.Found.WaitingTimeSeconds
histogram.summary: The wall-clock time spent waiting for the LAN-wide number of p2p downloads (i.e. the sum of p2p downloads from each peer on the LAN) to drop below the threshold. This is reported after examining responses from all peers on the LAN and picking a candidate.

histogram.name: P2P.Client.LookupResult
histogram.summary: The result of the lookup. Possible values include "Found" (if a candidate - i.e. a peer offering at least N bytes of file X - was chosen), "Not Found" (if no candidate could be found), "Vanished" (if a candidate was found but vanished while waiting in line), "Canceled" (if a candidate was found but the request was canceled while waiting in line), and "Filtered" (if it was detected that mDNS was filtered). This is reported after examining responses from all peers on the LAN when p2p is used to find a candidate.

histogram.name: P2P.Client.NumPeers
histogram.summary: The number of peers implementing p2p file sharing on the network. This is reported every time p2p is used to look up a resource on a network where mDNS is not filtered.

histogram.name: P2P.Client.Vanished.WaitingTimeSeconds
histogram.summary: The wall-clock time spent waiting for one or more candidates (i.e. peers offering at least N bytes of file X) that all vanished before the LAN-wide number of p2p downloads dropped below the threshold. This is reported every time candidates were found using p2p but then vanished.

histogram.name: P2P.Server.ClientCount
histogram.summary: The number of currently connected HTTP clients. This is reported every time a HTTP client connects.

histogram.name: P2P.Server.ContentServedInterruptedMB
histogram.summary: Number of megabytes (1,000,000 bytes) served from the device (via HTTP) where the client disconnects prematurely. This is reported every time a file is served and the client disconnects before receiving all data.

histogram.name: P2P.Server.ContentServedSuccessfullyMB
histogram.summary: Number of megabytes (1,000,000 bytes) served from the device (via HTTP). This is reported every time a file have been served successfully.

histogram.name: P2P.Server.DownloadSpeedKBps
histogram.summary: The average speed at which the download was served at, in kB/s. This is reported every time a file have been served successfully.

histogram.name: P2P.Server.FileCount
histogram.summary: The number of files available via p2p. This is reported every time a file is added or removed to the /var/cache/p2p directory.

histogram.name: P2P.Server.RangeBeginPercentage
histogram.summary: When a client resumes a download, the HTTP request includes range specifier to skip the bytes it already has. This metric conveys this as a percentage of the the file size. This is reported every time a file is served, even if the request does not include a range specifier (in which case 0 is reported).

histogram.name: P2P.Server.RequestResult
histogram.summary: The result of the HTTP request. Possible values include "Response Sent" (the resource was found and the response was successfully sent), "Response Interrupted" (the resource was found but the client disconnected), "Malformed" (the request was malformed), "Not Found" (the request was for a resource that was not found), and "Index" (the request was for the '/' or '/index.html' resource). This is reported for every HTTP request handled.

histogram.name: PasswordGeneration.UploadStarted
histogram.summary: The number of times that we try to upload a form that we believe should trigger password generation. False means that something about the form would not allow us to try upload (not an Autofillable field, uploading disabled, Autofill servers in backoff, etc.). True does not mean that the upload actually completed successfully, just that it was started.

histogram.name: PasswordManager.AccountsPerSite

histogram.name: PasswordManager.ActionsTakenWithPsl

histogram.name: PasswordManager.BlacklistedSites

histogram.name: PasswordManager.Enabled

histogram.name: PasswordManager.NumPasswordsNotShown

histogram.name: PasswordManager.SavePasswordPromptDisappearedQuickly

histogram.name: PasswordManager.TimesPasswordUsed

histogram.name: PasswordManager.TotalAccounts

histogram.name: PerformanceMonitor.AverageCPU.BrowserProcess

A value of 12 indicates an error parsing dmesg and should be investigated. See also Platform.LotIdEnum.

histogram.name: Platform.DiskUsageChronos

histogram.name: Platform.DiskUsageVar

histogram.name: Platform.IntelMaxMicroArchitecture
histogram.summary: The maximum supported micro-architecture on an Intel platform. This value is logged at program start time.

histogram.name: Platform.KernelWarningHashes
histogram.summary: The 32-bit hash of a kernel warning. This is the hash of the "file:line" string corresponding to the location of the warning, for instance: "/mnt/host/source/src/third_party/kernel/files/drivers /gpu/drm/i915/intel_dp.c:351" (ignore spurious spaces). The hash is produced by this code: while (*string) hash = (hash << 5) + hash + *string++; Separately each warning is also collected (with its hash) via the crash reporter, but only its first occurrence in each boot session. Contact semenzato@ for further info.

histogram.name: Platform.LogicalCpuCount

histogram.name: Platform.LotIdEnum
histogram.summary: Chrome OS (ARM Chromebooks using Exynos 5250 only) indication about whether we're part of a special lot ID. Special lot IDs are groups of chips that have special case handling in the kernel for the Adaptive Support Voltage code (the normal logic doesn't work). See also Platform.AsvGroup. Note that fused devices are never part of a special lot (currently) and only some unfused lots are "special".

histogram.name: Platform.SmartUncorrectableErrors

histogram.name: Platform.SpringChargerType
histogram.summary:
USB device ID of the charger plugged into a Spring device (if any), sent once a minute. The Device ID is composed from the following 4 8-bit registers of the TSU6721 chip: ADC (07h), Device Type 3 (15h), Device Type 2 (0Bh), Device Type 1 (0Ah). Device Type 1/2/3 is a bitmap and most of bits are mutually exclusive (excepted VBUS debounce). ADC is the 5-bit value of the ID pin, but for most types (as in Device Type), there are only one or two possible ID pin connections/values. The datasheet can be found here: http://www.ti.com/lit/ds/symlink/tsu6721.pdf.
Note that different brand/models of the charger can have the same ID.

histogram.name: Platform.WriteSectorsShort
histogram.summary: Number of disk sectors per second written by Chrome OS in a short interval (currently 1s, sampled every 30s)

histogram.name: PLT.BeginToFirstPaint
histogram.summary: Time from "begin" to "first paint." "Begin"== "request" if user requested, and "start" otherwise. "Request"== time when user requested document. "Start"== time when renderer requested load of document, after any unload of last document. "First paint"== time when first paint operation was performed.

histogram.name: PLT.CommitToFirstPaint
histogram.summary: Time from "commit" to "first paint." "Commit"== time when renderer got first byte of document. "First paint"== time when first paint operation was performed.

histogram.name: PLT.LoadType
histogram.summary: Probability distribution for enumerated varieties of page loads.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_Connect
histogram.summary: Time from connectStart to connectEnd based on Navigation Timing.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_DelayBeforeConnect
histogram.summary: Time from domanLookupEnd to connectStart based on Navigation Timing.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_DelayBeforeDomainLookup
histogram.summary: Time from fetchStart to domainLookupStart based on Navigation Timing.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_DelayBeforeDomLoading
histogram.summary: Time from responseStart to domLoading based on Navigation Timing.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_DelayBeforeFetch
histogram.summary: Time from navigationStart to fetchStart based on Navigation Timing when no redirect.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_DelayBeforeFetchRedirect
histogram.summary: Time from navigationStart to fetchStart excluding time spent on redirects based on Navigation Timing. Only page loads with redirects are considered.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_DelayBeforeLoadEvent
histogram.summary: Time from domContentLoadedEventEnd to loadEventStart based on Navigation Timing.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_DelayBeforeRequest
histogram.summary: Time from connectEnd to requestStart based on Navigation Timing.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_DomainLookup
histogram.summary: Time from domainLookupStart to domainLookupEnd based on Navigation Timing.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_DomContentLoaded
histogram.summary: Time from domContentLoadedEventStart to domContentLoadedEventEnd based on Navigation Timing.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_DomInteractive
histogram.summary: Time from domInteractive to domContentLoadEventStart based on Navigation Timing.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_DomLoading
histogram.summary: Time from domLoading to domInteractive based on Navigation Timing.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_LoadEvent
histogram.summary: Time from loadEventStart to loadEventEnd based on Navigation Timing.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_Redirect
histogram.summary: Time from redirectStart to redirectEnd based on Navigation Timing when redirects exist.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_Request
histogram.summary: Time from requestStart to responseStart based on Navigation Timing.

histogram.name: PLT.NT_Response
histogram.summary: Time from responseStart to responseEnd based on Navigation Timing.

histogram.name: PLT.PerceivedLoadTime
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 5/02/2011, replaced by Prerender.RendererPLT.
histogram.summary: Perceived load time of a page. For non-prerendered pages, this is just BeginToFinish. For displayed prerendered pages, this is the time from when the prerendered page is moved into a TabContents until finish. "Finish" == after onload() and all resources are loaded. Note that this is 0 if the loading finishes before the page is moved into a TabContents.

histogram.name: PLT.PerceivedLoadTime_PrerenderLoad
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 5/02/2011, replaced by Prerender.RendererPerceivedPLTMatched.
histogram.summary: Perceived load time of a prerendered page that is displayed. This is the time from when the prerendered page is moved into a TabContents until finish. "Finish" == after onload() and all resources are loaded. Note that this is 0 if the loading finishes before the the page is moved into a TabContents.

histogram.name: PLT.PT_BeginToCommit
histogram.summary: This time is based on the NavigationTiming spec and is a more accurate version of PLT.BeginToCommit. Commit: responseStart. Begin: requestStart or navigationStart if user-initiated request.

histogram.name: PLT.PT_BeginToFinish
histogram.summary: This time is based on the NavigationTiming spec and is a more accurate version of PLT.BeginToFinish. Finish: loadEventEnd. Begin: requestStart or navigationStart if user-initiated request.

histogram.name: PLT.PT_BeginToFinishDoc
histogram.summary: This time is based on the NavigationTiming spec and is a more accurate version of PLT.BeginToFinishDoc. FinishDoc: loadEventStart. Begin: requestStart or navigationStart if user-initiated request.

histogram.name: PLT.PT_CommitToFinish
histogram.summary: This time is based on the NavigationTiming spec and is a more accurate version of PLT.CommitToFinish. Commit: responseStart. Finish: loadEventEnd.

histogram.name: PLT.PT_CommitToFinishDoc
histogram.summary: This time is based on the NavigationTiming spec and is a more accurate version of PLT.CommitToFinishDoc. Commit: responseStart. FinishDoc: loadEventStart.

histogram.name: PLT.PT_FinishDocToFinish
histogram.summary: This time is based on the NavigationTiming spec and is a more accurate version of PLT.FinishDocToFinish. Finish: loadEventEnd. FinishDoc: loadEventStart.

histogram.name: PLT.PT_RequestToCommit
histogram.summary: This time is based on the NavigationTiming spec and measures the time until the renderer got first byte of document. Commit: time when renderer got first byte of document. Request: navigationStart.

histogram.name: PLT.PT_RequestToDomContentLoaded
histogram.summary: This time is based on the NavigationTiming spec and measures the time until the beginning of the DOMContentLoaded event. DOMContentLoaded: domContentLoadedEventStart. Request: navigationStart.

histogram.name: PLT.PT_RequestToFinish
histogram.summary: This time is based on the NavigationTiming spec and is a more accurate version of PLT.RequestToFinish. Finish: loadEventEnd. Request: navigationStart.

histogram.name: PLT.PT_RequestToFinishDoc
histogram.summary: This time is based on the NavigationTiming spec and measures the page load time until the beginning of the load event. Finish: loadEventStart. Request: navigationStart.

histogram.name: PLT.PT_RequestToStart
histogram.summary: This time is based on the NavigationTiming spec and is a more accurate version of PLT.RequestToStart. Start: requestStart. Request: navigationStart.

histogram.name: PLT.PT_StartToCommit
histogram.summary: This time is based on the NavigationTiming spec and is a more accurate version of PLT.StartToCommit. Start: requestStart. Commit: responseStart.

histogram.name: PLT.PT_StartToFinish
histogram.summary: This time is based on the NavigationTiming spec and is a more accurate version of PLT.StartToFinish. Start: requestStart. Finish: loadEventEnd.

histogram.name: PLT.RequestToFinish
histogram.summary: Time from "request" to "finish." "Request" == time when user requested document. "Finish" == after onload() and all resources are loaded.

histogram.name: PLT.StartToCommit
histogram.summary: Time from "start" to "commit." "Start"== time when renderer requested load of document, after any unload of last document. "Commit"== time when renderer got first byte of document.

histogram.name: PLT.StartToFinish
histogram.summary: Time from "start" to "finish." "Start"== time when renderer requested load of document, after any unload of last document. "Finish"==after onload() and all resources are loaded.

histogram.name: PLT.UserTiming_Mark
histogram.summary: This time is based on the User Timing spec and measures the time from Navigation Timing navigationStart until the point where the page called performance.mark().

histogram.name: PLT.UserTiming_MeasureDuration
histogram.summary: This time is based on the User Timing spec and reports the time between two arbitrary points defined by the page being loaded and directly matches the measurement exposed by performance.measure().

histogram.name: Plugin.FlashNavigateUsage

histogram.name: Plugin.PpapiBrokerLoadResult
histogram.summary: The result from an attempt to load a PPAPI broker.

histogram.name: Plugin.PpapiPluginLoadResult
histogram.summary: The result from an attempt to load a PPAPI plugin.

histogram.name: Power.BacklightLevelOnAC
histogram.summary: The level of the backlight as a percentage when the user is on AC. Sampled every 30 seconds.

histogram.name: Power.BacklightLevelOnBattery
histogram.summary: The level of the backlight as a percentage when the user is on battery. Sampled every 30 seconds.

histogram.name: Power.BatteryChargeHealth
histogram.summary: Chrome OS battery charge health percentage. Sampled once when device starts charging.

histogram.name: Power.BatteryDischargeRate
histogram.summary: Chrome OS battery discharge rate in mW sampled every 30 seconds while the device runs on battery.

histogram.name: Power.BatteryDischargeRateWhileSuspended
histogram.summary: Chrome OS battery discharge rate in mW while the system was suspended, sampled at resume. Only reported if the system was on battery power both before suspending and after resuming, if the energy level didn't increase while suspended (which would indicate that an AC adapter was connected), and if the system was suspended for at least a minute.

histogram.name: Power.BatteryInfoSample
histogram.summary: Counts the number of times we have read the battery status from sysfs and if it gave us sensible values.

histogram.name: Power.BatteryRemainingAtEndOfSessionOnAC
histogram.summary: Chrome OS remaining battery charge as percent of the maximum battery charge, sampled at the end of a user session when the device is on AC.

histogram.name: Power.BatteryRemainingAtEndOfSessionOnBattery
histogram.summary: Chrome OS remaining battery charge as percent of the maximum battery charge, sampled at the end of a user session when the device is on battery.

histogram.name: Power.BatteryRemainingAtStartOfSessionOnAC
histogram.summary: Chrome OS remaining battery charge as percent of the maximum battery charge, sampled at the start of a user session when the device is on AC.

histogram.name: Power.BatteryRemainingAtStartOfSessionOnBattery
histogram.summary: Chrome OS remaining battery charge as percent of the maximum battery charge, sampled at the start of a user session when the device is on battery.

histogram.name: Power.BatteryRemainingCharge
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 03/2012, no longer being generated by powerd.
histogram.summary: Chrome OS remaining battery charge as percent of the maximum battery charge sampled when the device runs on battery.

histogram.name: Power.BatteryRemainingWhenChargeStarts
histogram.summary: Chrome OS remaining battery charge as percent of the maximum battery charge, sampled when charging starts.

histogram.name: Power.BatteryTimeToEmpty
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 03/2012, no longer being generated by powerd.
histogram.summary: Chrome OS remaining time to empty battery in minutes sampled when the device runs on battery.

histogram.name: Power.BitfixChunks
histogram.summary: Chrome OS (Snow RO firmware 2695.90.0 only) number of 8K chunks that were fixed (memory corruption corrected) for each suspend/resume cycle. Expect 0 around 97% of the time and a non-zero value around 3% of the time.

histogram.name: Power.BitfixFixes
histogram.summary: Chrome OS (Snow RO firmware 2695.90.0 only) number of 4-byte words that were fixed (memory corruption corrected) for each suspend/resume cycle. Expect 0 around 97% of the time and a non-zero value around 3% of the time. Would be exactly equal to Power.BitfixChunks if there were only one corrupted word in each chunk but is sometimes several times higher.

histogram.name: Power.BrightnessAdjustOnAC
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 5/2013. See Accel_BrightnessDown_F6 and Accel_BrightnessUp_F7 user actions instead.
histogram.summary: Number of times the user has adjusted brightness up and down while running on battery power.

histogram.name: Power.BrightnessAdjustOnBattery
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 5/2013. See Accel_BrightnessDown_F6 and Accel_BrightnessUp_F7 user actions instead.
histogram.summary: Number of times the user has adjusted brightness up and down while running on AC power.

histogram.name: Power.ChargerType
histogram.summary: External power supply type such as MAINS_CHARGER, USB_CHARGER, UNCONFIRMED_SPRING_CHARGER, SAFE_SPRING_CHARGER. A sample is reported each time a charger is connected to the device.

histogram.name: Power.FirmwareResumeTimeOnAC
histogram.summary: The time that the firmware took to resume the Chrome OS device from suspend-to-RAM state when running on AC at pre-suspend time.

histogram.name: Power.FirmwareResumeTimeOnBattery
histogram.summary: The time that the firmware took to resume the Chrome OS device from suspend-to-RAM state when running on battery at pre-suspend time.

histogram.name: Power.IdleTimeAfterDimOnAC
histogram.summary: Chrome OS user idle time since the screen dimmed sampled when the user becomes active again if the device runs on AC.

histogram.name: Power.IdleTimeAfterDimOnBattery
histogram.summary: Chrome OS user idle time since the screen dimmed sampled when the user becomes active again if the device runs on battery.

histogram.name: Power.IdleTimeAfterScreenOffOnAC
histogram.summary: Chrome OS user idle time since the screen turned off sampled when the user becomes active again if the device runs on AC.

histogram.name: Power.IdleTimeAfterScreenOffOnBattery
histogram.summary: Chrome OS user idle time since the screen turned off sampled when the user becomes active again if the device runs on battery.

histogram.name: Power.IdleTimeOnAC
histogram.summary: Chrome OS user idle time sampled when the user becomes active again if the device runs on AC.

histogram.name: Power.IdleTimeOnBattery
histogram.summary: Chrome OS user idle time sampled when the user becomes active again if the device runs on battery.

histogram.name: Power.KernelResumeTimeOnAC
histogram.summary: The time that the kernel took to resume the Chrome OS device from suspend-to-RAM state when running on AC at pre-suspend time.

histogram.name: Power.KernelResumeTimeOnBattery
histogram.summary: The time that the kernel took to resume the Chrome OS device from suspend-to-RAM state when running on battery at pre-suspend time.

histogram.name: Power.KernelSuspendTimeOnAC
histogram.summary: The time that the kernel took to suspend-to-RAM the Chrome OS device when running on AC.

histogram.name: Power.KernelSuspendTimeOnBattery
histogram.summary: The time that the kernel took to suspend-to-RAM the Chrome OS device when running on battery.

histogram.name: Power.KeyboardBacklightLevel
histogram.summary: The level of the keyboard backlight as a percentage. Sampled every 30 seconds.

histogram.name: Power.LengthOfSession
histogram.summary: The length of time, in seconds, that a user spent in a single session. Values for this metric are clamped to 12 hours, so the last bucket should be considered to be including all metrics above 12 hours.

histogram.name: Power.MilliConsumptionPerHourIosOnActive
histogram.summary: The average power consumption, measured in milli-units per hour, when sync invalidator listens to on_application_active events. Values for this metric are per session, i.e. from battery level at application entering foreground to returning to background, and normalized to an hourly average consumption. This is an iOS only measurement. Due to how iOS reports battery levels, it is likely to see many readings of 0.

histogram.name: Power.MilliConsumptionPerHourOthers
histogram.summary: The average power consumption, measured in milli-units per hour, for other sync invalidator methods. Values for this metric are per session, i.e. from battery level at application entering foreground to returning to background, and normalized to an hourly average consumption. This is an iOS only measurement. Due to how iOS reports battery levels, it is likely to see many readings of 0.

histogram.name: Power.MilliConsumptionPerHourP2P
histogram.summary: The average power consumption, measured in milli-units per hour, when sync invalidator uses peer-to-peer notifications. Values for this metric are per session, i.e. from battery level at application entering foreground to returning to background, and normalized to an hourly average consumption. This is an iOS only measurement. Due to how iOS reports battery levels, it is likely to see many readings of 0.

histogram.name: Power.MilliConsumptionPerHourServer
histogram.summary: The average power consumption, measured in milli-units per hour, when sync invalidator uses server-based non-blocking invalidator. Values for this metric are per session, i.e. from battery level at application entering foreground to returning to background, and normalized to an hourly average consumption. This is an iOS only measurement. Due to how iOS reports battery levels, it is likely to see many readings of 0.

histogram.name: Power.NumberOfAlsAdjustmentsPerSession
histogram.summary: The number of times that the Automatic Light Sensor (ALS) adjusted the brightness during a session. Values for this metric are clamped to 10k count, so the last bucket should be considered to be including all metrics above 10k.

histogram.name: Power.NumberOfSessionsPerCharge
histogram.summary: The number of user sessions that occured since the last time that the device was charged. Values for this metric are clamped at 10k, so the last bucket should be considered to include all metrics about 10k.

histogram.name: Power.RetrySuspendCount
histogram.summary: The number of times Chrome OS retried suspend due to previous failure.

histogram.name: Power.SuspendStatus
histogram.summary: ChromeOS suspend status - either success, failure, or cancelled.

histogram.name: Power.ThermalAbortedFanTurnOn
histogram.summary: The percentage of aborted fan attempts out of total fan attempts per session, where an abort is due to hysteresis. This value is computed from boot and sent when powerd starts and then every 15 minutes afterwards.

histogram.name: Power.ThermalMultipleFanTurnOn
histogram.summary: The percentage of fan trip point passes that are more than one trip point. This value is computed from boot and sent when powerd starts and then every 15 minutes afterwards.

histogram.name: Power.TimeInSuspendAtBoot
histogram.summary: Chrome OS time in minutes spent in suspend-to-RAM mode sampled at boot (i.e., the device most likely ran out of battery while in suspend).

histogram.name: Power.TimeInSuspendAtResume
histogram.summary: Chrome OS time in minutes spent in suspend-to-RAM mode sampled at resume.

histogram.name: Power.UserBrightnessAdjustmentsPerSessionOnAC
histogram.summary: The number of times that the user adjusted the brightness during a session when on AC. Values for this metric are clamped to 10k count, so the last bucket should be considered to be including all metrics above 10k.

histogram.name: Power.UserBrightnessAdjustmentsPerSessionOnBattery
histogram.summary: The number of times that the user adjusted the brightness during a session when on battery. Values for this metric are clamped to 10k count, so the last bucket should be considered to be including all metrics above 10k.

histogram.name: Precache.DownloadedNonPrecache
histogram.summary: The number of bytes that were downloaded over the network for HTTP/HTTPS fetches that were not motivated by precaching. Logged per-request.

histogram.name: Precache.DownloadedPrecacheMotivated
histogram.summary: The number of bytes that were downloaded because of precaching. Logged per-request.

histogram.name: Precache.Saved
histogram.summary: The number of bytes during user browsing that were served from the cache, but would have been downloaded over a network if precaching was disabled. Logged per-request.

histogram.name: Prerender.Event
histogram.summary: Enumeration of what events related to prerendering have occurred.

histogram.name: Prerender.Events

histogram.summary: Hover Event counts for prerendering.

histogram.name: Prerender.FinalStatus
histogram.summary: Final status for prerender pages - either success, or why it was canceled.

histogram.name: Prerender.FinalStatusMatchComplete
histogram.summary: Final status for prerender pages - either success, or why it was canceled. This is for the MatchComplete set of pages (including some pages that were not actually prerendered), to match the control group.

histogram.name: Prerender.FractionPixelsFinalAtSwapin
histogram.summary: For prerenders that are swapped in, the percentage of pixels that is already final at swap-in time compared to when the spinner stops.

histogram.name: Prerender.HoverStats_TimeUntilClicked
histogram.obsolete: deprecated May 10 2012
histogram.summary:
Duration that a user hovers a link before clicking on it.
This is recorded for all pages loaded in a session.

Duration that the mouse pointer hovers on a link before the mouse pointer moves off of it.
This is recorded for all pages loaded in a session.

histogram.summary: Enumeration of what events related to the local predictor have occurred

histogram.name: Prerender.LocalPredictorLoggedInLookupTime
histogram.summary: Time to perform the LoggedIn Lookup for the local predictor. This operation checks whether a user his likely logged into a page that we would like to prerender.

histogram.name: Prerender.LocalPredictorServiceLookupTime
histogram.summary: Time to perform the Service Lookup for the local predictor. This operation queries a Google service to obtain pages to prerender, as well as whether prerender candidate pages are likely safe for prerendering.

histogram.name: Prerender.LocalPredictorTimeUntilUsed
histogram.summary: Time from when a prerendered page is started to when it is first used due to user navigation. If the page is never used, it is not included in this histogram. This only refers to prerenders based on the local predictor.

histogram.name: Prerender.LocalPredictorURLLookupTime
histogram.summary: Time to perform the URL Lookup for the local predictor. This operation retrieves from the user's local browsing history the URLs corresponding to URLIDs.

histogram.name: Prerender.LocalVisitCoreTransition
histogram.obsolete: deprecated Nov 16 2012
histogram.summary: The transition type for each new visit as recorded in the local visits database.

histogram.name: Prerender.LocalVisitDatabaseSize
histogram.obsolete: deprecated Nov 16 2012
histogram.summary: Size of the local visits database (number of entries).

histogram.name: Prerender.LocalVisitEvents
histogram.obsolete: deprecated Nov 16 2012
histogram.summary: Enumeration of what events related to local visits have occurred

histogram.name: Prerender.ModPagespeedHeader
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated as of 10/2013.
histogram.summary: Previous version of the Prerender.PagespeedHeader.* histograms.

histogram.name: Prerender.OmniboxNavigationsCouldPrerender
histogram.summary: A boolean that indicates whether the Omnibox navigation being committed could have been prerendered by the Omnibox Prerender system. This provides an upper bound for Prerender.OmniboxNavigationsUsedPrerenderCount and allows the potential for Omnibox Prerendering coverage to be understood. If Omnibox Prerendering is disabled, this histogram will register a 'false' entry. The total count is the equivalent of the deprecated NetworkActionPredictor.NavigationCount histogram.

histogram.name: Prerender.OmniboxNavigationsUsedPrerenderCount
histogram.summary: The number of navigations that use a prerender initiated from the Omnibox. The count is incremented when the Prerendered tab is swapped in if the Prerender was initiated by the Omnibox, which obviously requires Prerendering from the Omnibox to be enabled.

histogram.name: Prerender.OmniboxPrerenderCount
histogram.summary: The number of prerenders initiated from the Omnibox. This is incremented when the NetworkActionPredictor suggests Prerendering as an optimal strategy given the text the user has entered and the Autocomplete suggestion currently selected. It is only incremented if Prerendering from the Omnibox is enabled.

histogram.name: Prerender.PagespeedHeader.ServerCounts
histogram.summary: The number of responses received bucketed into the range [0,4]: bucket 0 is the total number of responses received; bucket 1 is the number of responses received with an X-Mod-Pagespeed header [indicating a mod_pagespeed server]; bucket 2 is the number of responses received with an X-Page-Speed header and a header value in the X-Mod-Pagespeed format (a.b.c.d-e) [indicating an ngx_pagespeed server]; bucket 3 is the number of responses received with an X-Page-Speed header and a header value in the PageSpeed Service format (a_b_c) [indicating a PSS server]; and bucket 4 is the number of responses received with an X-Page-Speed header and a header value in neither of the preceding formats [indicating some other server; IISpeed is the only known one at this stage].

histogram.name: Prerender.PagespeedHeader.VersionCounts
histogram.summary: The number of responses received that either have an X-Mod-Pagespeed header or have an X-Page-Speed header with a value in the X-Mod-Pagespeed format (a.b.c.d-e), bucketed into the range [1,99]: bucket 1 is for header values that aren't in the a.b.c.d-e format, the remaining buckets are an encoding of the value: 2 + 2 * (max(c, 10) - 10) + (d > 1 ? 1 : 0). The rationale is that 'c' is incremented with each new release and 'd' is initially 0 but is incremented for each patch to a release.

histogram.name: Prerender.PageviewEvents
histogram.obsolete: deprecated Nov 16 2012
histogram.summary: Types of pages rendered.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPageLoadTime_Control
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated 03/24/11. Replaced by Prerender.PerceivedPLT_ContentPrefetchPrerenderControl.
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
This particular histogram is for all page loads for users who do not have prerendering enabled.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPageLoadTime_PrerenderMatchControl
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated 03/24/11. Replaced by Prerender.PerceivedPLTMatched_ContentPrefetchPrerenderControl.
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
This particular histogram is only for pages that would have been prerendered if the user had prerender enabled.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPageLoadTime_PrerenderMatchTreatment
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated 03/24/11. Replaced by Prerender.PerceivedPLTMatched_ContentPrefetchPrerender.
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
This particular histogram is for all prerendered page loads for users who have prerender enabled.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPageLoadTime_Treatment
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated 03/24/11. Replaced by Prerender.PerceivedPLT_ContentPrefetchPrerender.
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
This particular histogram is for all page loads for users who have prerendering enabled.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPageLoadTime_WindowControl
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated 03/24/11. Replaced by Prerender.PerceivedPLTWindowed_ContentPrefetchPrerenderControl.
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
This particular histogram is for all page loads within 30 seconds after a prefetch tag is seen for users who do not have prerendering enabled.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPageLoadTime_WindowTreatment
histogram.obsolete: Deprecated 03/24/11. Replaced by Prerender.PerceivedPLTWindowed_ContentPrefetchPrerender.
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load pre navigation.
This particular histogram is for all page loads within 30 seconds after a prefetch tag is seen for users who have prerendering enabled.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPLT
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
This is recorded for all pages loaded in a session.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPLTFirstAfterMiss
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
This is recorded for the first page load completing immediately after a prerender.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPLTFirstAfterMissAnyOnly
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
"FirstAfterMiss" means the first pageload after a prerender miss. There are two types: Any, and Non-overlapping. The latter only applies to page loads initiated after the prerender. This variable records cases where only Any triggered.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPLTFirstAfterMissBoth
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
"FirstAfterMiss" means the first pageload after a prerender miss. There are two types: Any, and Non-overlapping. The latter only applies to page loads initiated after the prerender. This variable records cases where both triggered.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPLTFirstAfterMissNonOverlapping
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
This is recorded for the first page load completing immediately after a prerender, but which has also started after the prerender has been initiated.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPLTFirstAfterMissNonOverlappingOnly
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
"FirstAfterMiss" means the first pageload after a prerender miss. There are two types: Any, and Non-overlapping. The latter only applies to page loads initiated after the prerender. This variable records cases where only Non-overlapping triggered.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPLTMatched
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
This is recorded only for prerendered pages, or for pages which would have been prerendered in the control case.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPLTMatchedComplete
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
This is recorded only for prerendered pages, or for pages which would have been prerendered in the control case.
In MatchedComplete, the prerender group also contains cancelled prerenders, so as to produce a perfect match of page views attributed this group in the prerender group with those attributed to this group in the control group.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPLTWindowed
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
This is recorded for all page loads which happen within 30 seconds after a prefetch tag is observed.

histogram.name: Prerender.PerceivedPLTWindowNotMatched
histogram.summary:
Time from when a user navigates to a page to when it loads. Since the pages may start loading before the user navigates to it, this does not include any portion of load prior to navigation.
This is recorded for all page loads which happen within 30 seconds after a prefetch tag is observed and which do not correspond to a prerender tag.

histogram.name: Prerender.PercentLoadDoneAtSwapin
histogram.summary: For prerenders that are swapped in, the percentage of the time from load start until the onload event fires that has elapsed at the time of the swapin.

histogram.name: Prerender.PeriodicCleanupDeleteContentsTime

histogram.name: Prerender.PeriodicCleanupResourceCheckTime
histogram.summary: How long the resource check portion of PrerenderManager::PeriodicCleanup takes, to measure jank.

histogram.name: Prerender.PrerenderCountOf3Max
histogram.summary: After launching a prerender, how many simultanious prerenders are recorded as running, out of a maximum of three.

histogram.name: Prerender.PrerenderNotSwappedInPLT
histogram.summary: For prerenders that finish loading before they are ever swapped in, their page load time until the onload event fires.

histogram.name: Prerender.PrerendersPerSessionCount

histogram.name: Prerender.RendererPerceivedPLT

For displayed prerendered pages, this is the time from when the prerendered page is moved into a TabContents until finish. "Finish" == after onload() and all resources are loaded. histogram.name: Profile.SupervisedProfileTotalCreateTime
histogram.summary: Time elapsed from when the handler received the message that a user clicked 'Create' to create a new supervised user profile until the registration ends either successfully or with a failure (both recorded in Profile.SupervisedProfileCreateResult).

histogram.name: Profile.SupervisedProfileTotalImportTime
histogram.summary: Time elapsed from when the handler received the message that a user clicked 'Import supervised user' until the registration ends either successfully or with a failure (both recorded in Profile.SupervisedProfileImportResult).

histogram.name: SB2.GetHashResult
histogram.summary: Track return status from GetHash requests to server (STATUS_200 and STATUS_204), and dispensation of returned values (EMPTY, HIT, MISS). EMPTY means the response had no full hashes, and should contain all of the 204 responses plus those 200 responses corrosponding to items deleted on the server but not yet deleted on the client. HIT means that one of the full hashes matched. MISS means that none of the hashes matched (there was a prefix collision).

histogram.name: SB2.GetHashResultDownload
histogram.summary: Track return status from GetHash requests to server (STATUS_200 and STATUS_204), and dispensation of returned values (EMPTY, HIT, MISS). EMPTY means the response had no full hashes, and should contain all of the 204 responses plus those 200 responses corrosponding to items deleted on the server but not yet deleted on the client. HIT means that one of the full hashes matched. MISS means that none of the hashes matched (there was a prefix collision).

histogram.name: SBClientPhishing.ClientModelStatus
histogram.summary: The counts for various model status codes that we get after loading a new client-side phishing model.

histogram.name: SBClientPhishing.DOMFeatureChunkTime
histogram.summary: The time that an individual chunk of DOM feature extraction work took.

histogram.name: SBClientPhishing.DOMFeatureFrameRemoved
histogram.summary: The number of times that DOM feature extraction finished early because the active WebDocument's frame was removed during traversal.

histogram.name: SBClientPhishing.DOMFeatureIterations
histogram.summary: The number of iterations that the DOM feature extractor took to finish.

histogram.name: SBClientPhishing.DOMFeatureResumeTime
histogram.summary: The time that it took to resume DOM feature extraction for the phishing classifier. Longer times may indicate that the page DOM changed between chunks of work and the extractor had to re-traverse up to the saved position.

histogram.name: SBClientPhishing.DOMFeatureTimeout
histogram.summary: The number of phishing classifications that were aborted because DOM feature extraction took too long.

histogram.name: SBClientPhishing.DOMFeatureTotalTime
histogram.summary: The time that the DOM feature extarctor took to finish, summed across all chunks of work.

histogram.name: SBClientPhishing.GrabPhishingThumbnail

histogram.summary: The number of times that a cached phishing classification result was used, rather than pinging the server.

histogram.name: SBClientPhishing.TermFeatureChunkTime
histogram.summary: The time that an individual chunk of term feature extraction work took.

histogram.name: SBClientPhishing.TermFeatureIterations
histogram.summary: The number of iterations that the term feature extractor took to finish.

histogram.name: SBClientPhishing.TermFeatureTimeout
histogram.summary: The number of phishing classification that were aborted because term feature extraction took too long.

histogram.name: SBClientPhishing.TermFeatureTotalTime
histogram.summary: The time that the term feature extarctor took to finish, summed across all chunks of work.

histogram.summary: The time taken to extract URL features for the phishing classifier.

histogram.name: SiteIsolation.AllResponses

histogram.name: SiteIsolation.BrowsingInstanceCount
histogram.summary: The count of all current BrowsingInstances. Recorded once per UMA ping.

histogram.name: SiteIsolation.CurrentRendererProcessCount
histogram.summary: The count of all renderer processes, including WebUI and extensions. Recorded once per UMA ping.

histogram.name: SiteIsolation.IsolateAllSitesProcessCountEstimate
histogram.summary: The upper bound of the predicted renderer process count if we isolated all sites, subject to the process limit. Recorded once per UMA ping.

histogram.name: SiteIsolation.IsolateAllSitesProcessCountLowerBound
histogram.summary: The lower bound of the predicted renderer process count if we isolated all sites, subject to the process limit. Happens to be the number of unique sites. Recorded once per UMA ping.

histogram.name: SiteIsolation.IsolateAllSitesProcessCountNoLimit
histogram.summary: The predicted renderer process count if we isolated all sites and if there were no process limit. Recorded once per UMA ping.

histogram.name: SiteIsolation.IsolateAllSitesTotalProcessCountEstimate
histogram.summary: The predicted total process count if we isolated all sites, subject to the process limit. Recorded once per UMA ping.

histogram.name: SiteIsolation.IsolateHttpsSitesProcessCountEstimate
histogram.summary: The upper bound of the predicted renderer process count if we isolated only HTTPS (not HTTP) sites, subject to the process limit. Recorded once per UMA ping.

histogram.name: SiteIsolation.IsolateHttpsSitesProcessCountLowerBound
histogram.summary: The lower bound of the predicted renderer process count if we isolated only HTTPS (not HTTP) sites, subject to the process limit. Happens to be the number of isolated sites. Recorded once per UMA ping.

histogram.name: SiteIsolation.IsolateHttpsSitesProcessCountNoLimit

histogram.name: SiteIsolation.IsolateHttpsSitesTotalProcessCountEstimate

histogram.name: SiteIsolation.XSD.DataLength
